Sender  Kokuei~
Date    Sun Mar 26 23:45:35 2000~
Stamp   954135935
To      Jurai~
Subject Application~
Text
``   Overhead shines the bright yellow star named Sol. As you survey the wavering green grass on the hill 
overlooking Ryoh's Lake, your eyes fall to a lone figure. Her black hair reaches to mid-back, and wavers 
slightly in the breeze. As you walk closer to her, you notice her light build. She couldn't be more than 
5 feet 10 inches tall. On her hip is a large sword, and strapped to her right thigh is a dagger. Her navy 
blue pants are tucked into black boots. She wears a rather unremarkable loose fitting black shirt. A 
glint catches your eye, and you then notice that she has a pendant around her neck, a sapphire gemstone 
in the shape of a star. Your gaze turns farther up and you see a rather distant, almost saddened look on 
her face. Her eyes, amethyst with streaks of silver and bright blue, tell a story of someone who has seen 
much hardship. You think for a moment to ask her what is troubling her, but remember your purpose. 
``   After a few moments time, she begins to speak. 'I am Kokuei, a Saiyan. The people of this world tend 
not to like my race... and understandably so. We have done some terrible things... Myself included.' 

``  A tear forms in the corner of her eye as she looks down at the lake. 'It was...oh, six years ago I'd 
say... I was still with my people then. I was on the space outpost in the Tau Ceti system where I was 
born when I received notice of my first mission. I was sent with five other Saiyans to subdue a planet 
called Karpiak. It was... it was a beautiful world. Purple skies, four moons...amazing place. Anyway, we 
were told that we were helping the 'true government' regain the power rebels had seized. During the 
mission, I was instructed to attack a massive warehouse that was supposedly holding terrorists. After I 
effectively flattened the building, I went in to examine the wreckage. I didn't find any terrorists.' 
``   Kokuei pauses and takes a slow, deep breath and wipes her eyes clear. 'What I found were children...it 
turns out that there were fifteen hundred in the warehouse. Fourteen hundred ninety-seven were killed in 
my initial attack. Two more died the next day from their injuries. There was one survivor... a woman 
whose name I now know is Bekka Sparks. In any case... The mission ended up failing... Outside forces 
intervened and my attack force was forced to flee. After the debriefing, I learned that my superiors knew 
that there were children in the warehouse, and that the military had a history of such 'targeting 
mistakes'. Also I learned that there were no rebels on Karpiak... We had attacked the rightful 
government. I... I lost faith in my commanders at that time... Called them liars and murderers...pirates. 
My fellow comrades turned against me...as did what was left of my family. My mother had died a few years 
before... Turns out she was killed by my own family for having much the same feelings I had come into.' 

``   She sighs and stares blankly for a few silent minutes. 'I assumed rightly that I didn't have much time 
left if I stayed among the Saiyans... So I stole one of the pod ships and left. The pod was damaged 
during my escape and the navigation system was damaged. By pure luck I crash-landed here on Earth, near a 
temple on the island of Hokkaido. I was taken in by the monks there and began to learn their ways, 
training to become a priestess. The faith is very much in touch with spirits and souls, especially those 
in the realm of fire. After three years with them, they presented me with this sword,'
``   'On my nineteenth birthday I was sent to Tokyo... They didn't say why, just that it was needed. 
Unfortunately...I didn't have time or opportunity to keep in practice of the faith. I developed quite a 
silly -aversion- to fire... Since after I left the temple I had a tendency to be lit on fire quite a 
bit.'
~
Sender  Kokuei~
Date    Sun Mar 26 23:56:43 2000~
Stamp   954136603
To      Jurai~
Subject Application(Cont)~
Text
``   Kokuei chuckles and smiles lightly. 'Six months passed...six months spent fighting the good 
fight...stopping slavers, killers, thieves, pirates...any kind of scum and villainy. Six months spent 
trying to make amends for the lives I took six years ago. I got far too many bruises and bumps to count. 
Eventually I stumbled upon a bar in Tokyo called Kansas...not much to speak of happened for a while, 
really. I made some friends...Ruka, Tyronos, Kurusa, Kuami, some others. One day, when myself, Tyronos,
Ruka, and Kurusa followed Kuami into a tomb/labyrinth built by one of her people. Ruka's body... was
inhabited by a malevolent soul. This soul truly manifested itself a few days later. Using a device built
by the temple called a soul trap, I was able to draw the soul out. When I did so... A detached piece of
Ruka's soul came with it. The shard of Ruka entered me moments before I destroyed
the trap, and the dark soul with it.'
``   She holds up her right hand, and you see a number of tiny scars on her palm. 'The crystal the trap was 
made out of did a number on my hand. I lost a lot of blood, and combining that with the amount of energy 
it took to crush the trap, I wasn't able to sense that the Ruka-shard had entered me. As the shard 
acquainted itself inside me, I was a little more violent and short-tempered than normal. It was again 
quiet for another few days. Then I met with Sirus Mekari. We talked for a while, and I told him about my 
training at the temple on Hokkaido. I also told him how Ruka said I was her best friend. That was when he 
asked me to do a reading on Ruka's soul. I did so... and found out about the missing shard. And found 
that it had gone into me. At the same time, Ruka received a letter from her father, Rendal Demaris... 
saying that he was coming home. A lot of the details on what happened are rather personal...but what I 
can say is that Rendal is a very, very evil man, and is coming after Ruka. And Sirus guessed that since I
had a shard of Ruka in me, he'd probably come after me too. So, after I retrieved one of the few 
remaining soul traps from the temple, Sirus and I used it to transfer a shard of his soul into me, to
hide the Ruka-shard.'
``   After looking up at the sky, Kokuei continues. 'But... In drawing the dark soul from Ruka's body, I 
had expended a tremendous amount of energy. It had temporarily tipped my mental and spiritual balance, 
which allowed the two soul shards I have in me to manifest themselves into... Alternate personalities 
would be the best term. The Ruka-shard had also begun bonding with my soul, which caused all sorts of new 
problems... the shard was very short tempered, but didn't have much control. When the Ruka-shard was in 
control of my body... she was very violent at times, but thankfully she didn't hurt anyone. 
Unfortunately, Rendal kept getting closer, and this forced the Sirus-shard to bond with my soul as well 
to help mask the Ruka-shard. Much of the imbalance created had yet to be repaired...and another couple 
days later my mind was flooded with memories from the Sirus-shard and to a lesser extent the Ruka-shard. 
This caused an immense amount of pain and the backlash allowed Rendal to find out that the Ruka-shard was 
in me. Sirus promised he'd protect me then, and made me promise not to go after Rendal. I've been a 
little unstable since then... I've come so close to giving into my fears and falling into the abyss. Ruka 
and Tyronos... They've been my anchors. Three or four days ago...I almost fell into the darkness again, 
and part of me welcomed it... But Tyronos...he saved me again. I...I owe him my life. We've grown 
pretty close since then...' 
~
Sender  Kokuei~
Date    Sun Mar 26 23:58:31 2000~
Stamp   954136711
To      Jurai~
Subject Application(Last section, I promise ;)~
Text
``   'There's so much injustice left in the world. I want to do more. So many innocents are getting hurt, 
and there's only so much I can do on my own. In any case, thanks for taking the time to listen to my
tale. Not many people around would do that.' 
``   Kokuei stares off into space, apparently lost in her own thoughts. After a few minutes, she notices 
