Sender  Cornelius~
Date    Sat Apr  8 22:57:30 2000~
Stamp   955252650
To      Mayaka~
Subject Elimination~
Text
I walked from the bar confident in my next job. A thief had hired me to eliminate a pesky elf in the area.
Such a simple job really. Just find and terminate the target. Only problem was I didn't know much other then
the target was an elf. The thief was pretty ignorant in that fact. I returned to my inn room and switched into
something a little lower profile. I picked out my favorite, brown trench coat, black pants, some shades, and 
my trusty sniper rifle. This baby had eliminated many targets over the years but it still had it's kick.
I left the in and traveled down the streets of Neo Tokyo. I spotted many elves but none that suited the weak
description I had received. I decided to stop in at a local tavern and see if I caould get some info on
the target. I learned that she was the leader of a small group and she had recently made trouble for a former client.
I also learned of where she lived. I slipped out of the tavern quietly and walked out of the city towards a valley.
This valley is known as the home of the elves so it seemed logical that she would be living here. I found a couple
guards on my way in, but they were quickly silenced. Their death cries rang in the night for miles around. I hoped
it hadn't alerted the target. I found a small cottage that fitted the description of her abode. I scaled the roof and
sit my rifle up, waiting for her to come home. I waited for nearly an hour when I saw the little elf walking towards
the house with several of her friends. I swiveled the rifle on it's base till the laser dot aimed directly over her
left lung. I like to let them suffer before they die. I pulled the trigger and the rifle kicked me in the shoulder,
hard. I saw the target fall and her friends rush to her side. There was no hope for her. All my bullets are tipped
with cyanide. I picked up my rifle and hopped down from the roof. I slipped off into the dark forest and made my way home.


Corkpyrian account of the assassination of the elven leader, Mayaka.
Mission accomplished. Payment in full. Cornelius, 1st class Corkpyian Alliance soldier, out of Alpha Centauri Omega base
~
Sender  Quillan~
Date    Sun Apr  9 03:53:25 2000~
Stamp   955270405
To      Kokuei~
Subject slid under your door...~
Text
Under your door you find an envelope inside is a small pin and a letter.  The letter reads:
"Dearest Kokuei,
It hasn't been long since I first met you but you mean a great deal to me.  A new challenge has arised that I must now face alone.
I wish I could find the words to tell you how much you have meant to me but they escape me, I hope that in time I will be strong enough to tell you everything. 
I am going away for a while, I must train myself, become stronger, and in a sence be reborn.
I will return one day, when I am stronger and a new man, the fight with Gelftree requires it.  I will be different in almost every aspect, but my feelings for you will remain constant.  
I write you this to tell you how I feel and why I must do what I am doing. Please, inform no one of what I have told you, I trust my heart and soul to you now.  Thank you Kokuei, thank you for being there for me. 
one day I hope we meet again, if you are asked...please tell the others only that I said, goodbye.
I must go now, my training begins and I have to leave to keep you and the others safe.  Goodbye Kokuei, I owe you my heart, when I return, it is yours for the taking.
Love,
Quillan
P.S.  The pin is the only thing I have that reminded me of who I am, please wear it and keep it safe untill I return for it.
Thank you"
~
