Sender  Zhilia~
Date    Sat Apr 22 21:44:01 2000~
Stamp   956457841
To      barius~
Subject Ressurection~
Text
I looked up at the complicated machinery, grinning. The thing was a cumbersome metallic monster, with wire and tube hair and long, claw-like appendages. At one end, sat a cylinder. At the other, a small claw.
The numerous buttons on the copy machine were blinking, signifying that the thing was doing what it was supposed to be doing. 
I clench my hands, and notice a small speck of human blood. Red, human blood. I grin inwardly, and I think back....

*Cool, black/white flashback*

"Hello, sir." I pleasantly said. I looked around the store. "Do you happen to have any copying machines around here?"
The man looked up from his newspaper. "What type, sir?"
I frowned. Technology wasn't exactly my expertise. "Well...I want a high-quality copying machine. That can take alot of pressure."
"Of course." the man bowed. "High-quality, eh? All right, sir. Please follow me."

"This is a Xerox Copying Machine, Model T-12, the best out there." the man warmly laid a hand on the small, printer-like thing.
And truth be told, that man didn't live long. And I had to go through fifteen different merchants before I finally fell upon a mad scientist type. He so kindly let me, err, 'borrow' is after some negotiation.

"NO! PLEASE! Anything, anything, anything but that! NooooOOOooO!!!" *sounds of tearing and dismemberment*

*End of flashback*

Now.... all I had to do was wait.
I twiddled my thumbs. I hummed 'Shabby is a gloomy old fellow'. Than, I followed up with '100 bottles of blood on the wall'.
The process for the copy cloning machine should not be rushed, or else the person copied might be.... immature, in more ways than emotionally. So I took my time....
And now, he looked almost complete. He drifted almost soundly in the murky green liquids in the tank. And the philosopher's stone, the Pledge Stone, the link between Barius and my mistress, Sortes, was in the claw to the right.
The philosopher's stone was legendary, because it was said to have come from the Sea of Chaos. If so.. it held tremendous powers. Powers I could have used. But.. my mistress instructed for me to give it to her new General. Barius.
So, now, Barius holds the power of the philosopher's stone, said to multiply the target's magical powers and aptitude by a factor of ten. And Barius was getting it.
Sometimes, I wondered, what would happen if i wrenched the stone out of the socket, to use for my own. Would the clone die prematurely? Probably.
So, now, I wait patiently, I wait for the rebirth of Barius, Ex-Seed Head Engineer, now a high-level Mazoku General, a rank as high as my own.... and I wait. Oh, and I managed to swipe somthing called 'TV' off of one merchant.... 
~
