Sender  Barius~
Date    Wed May 10 00:05:25 2000~
Stamp   957935125
To      Triss~
Subject In Kansas~
Text
Barius sat in the bar, drowning his troubles in a tall glass.  'Why does life have to be so hard...' he said quietly 
to himself, promptly before ordering another drink.  Barius looked around.  The bar was mostly empty, save himself, 
and another man, clad in a white shirt and blue jeans.  The man had a large two-handed bastard sword strapped 
tightly to his back.  The man noticed Barius looking at him, and Barius quickly looked back to his drink.  A couple
moments later, the man was sitting on the bas stool beside him, trying to strike up a conversation.

"Can I buy you a drink kid?"

Barius looked up quietly from his drink, and shook his head at the man.

"Im fine."

"You look tired kid, you havin' problems?"

"Something like that."

"Well, you don't seem very talkative, so I'll just leave you alone."

Both men went back to watching the large television, on a stand in the top corner of the bar.  The Canucks were 
TV shout out something like:
"We interrupt your daily schedualed program to bring you this important news bulletin.  Earlier today, in the 
south-western corner of Tokyo, a grisly scene was discovered.  In a small cathedral..."

Barius' ears perked up, and his head followed.

"...which many homeless people call their home, a mass-murder was committed.  Blood caked the walls of this very 
simple place, as if it was deleberately painted by the red stain of death.  Many bodies were found, including that
of the resident Father.  A suspect was witnessed fleeing the seen, but this is the only visible picture we have of 
him."

A picture of a man running off into an alley is shown on the screen, but it is mostly hard to see who it was through
the billowing red and black cape flowwing behind him.

"If you see this man, please report him to the local autorities immediately.  He is considered armed, and
dangerous"  The screen flickered back to the hockey game, and the Canucks were losing, go figure.

The man turned back to Barius, but surprisingly, found him not there.  The man picked up a cloth off of the stool
that Barius was sitting on.  "You forgot this!"  The man looked around carefully, and then incinerated the red and 
black cape in a burst of light.  "Heh..."  The man then dissappeared, his blue eyes glowing brightly.

Fortunately, neither of them saw you, watching carefully from one of the booths.
~
Sender  Alesh~
Date    Sat May 20 03:20:28 2000~
Stamp   958810828
To      Yoiko, Nomyuki, Thaais~
Subject Mixed state of emotion.~
Text
Alesh sat at her booth, crying heavily as she read the letter she'd recived from Kawaii.
All she could do was stare at the letter, every so often look at her ring as her thought's rolled out. 
`^'I don't understand. How is it you could possibly want me to stay? I mean, haven't I done enough harm already?``
`^'And now, you have me battling if a tough choice. I want to leave, so I never hurt you again, Kawaii..but..you want me to wait for you.'``
`^'But it may not matter, becuse I may be dead when you return. Thaais problably wants to kill me, and I know the hunters are close..or maybe even here.'``
`^'And Nomyuki...I don't know if I should feel sorry, or feel hate, or if I should feel at all. I know you simply tried to help me..it's all my fault'.``

Stops, and sighs, a heavy stream of tears running down her face. She looked around the room, at first looking for Kawaii.
She then looked around again...this time for Thaais, or the twins, or someone who wanted to come for her head.
`^Maybe..maybe it's best if I do die. Then, I won't hurt myself, or more importantly, anyone else. And, I oculd stop having to run that way.``
She nodded to herself, then smiled a little. `^'Yeah, that's the best thing. Kawaii, i'm so sorry for what i've done, and what i'm about to do. But, in the long run, i'll save you alot of pain.'``
`'I'm sorry, never meant to hurt any of you. Kawaii, you still mean the word to me. I do hope you can somehow forgive me.'``
`^'Thaais, please, I know you hate me more than anything right now. But, please believe me when I say it wasn't Nomyuki's fault.'``
`^'Nomyuki...you were a friend. Yes, there was a time when I wanted more than friendship, but that was to never happen. I'm sorry for any pain i've caused, I know you will never want to speak to me again.'``
Alesh folded the letter, and left the bar. She wasn't sure where she was headed, she half hoped it was somewhere to die. But..she also had hopes of returning once again to Kawaii, her loves, arms.
~
