Stamp   962941062
To      seityi~
Subject Note~
Text
Zhilia stumbles back into the Kansas bar, brushing away bits of dirt from his pants. Kiyara was very forceful when she wanted to be.

"See their house...my Mazoku demonic ass." Zhilia muttered, wedging his way throug hthe crowd until he got to his favorite table. There, he procured coffee and started writing.


"Dear Violent and Rascist Dragon--"

Crumple, crumple. Toss. Bull's eye.

"`1Dear Priestess Dragon,``"

Zhilia nibbles on the tip of his pencil, and writes slowly.

"`1Your anger for me is unbelievable, even from a priestess dragon of your caliber. Although I do not doubt your power, nor your hate for me, I wish to call a momentary truce.
At least hear me out with what I have to say. I am, indeed, a Mazoku, hated and feaed enemy of the golden dragons-- I'm sure your education has pumped enough legends and
folklore to tell you so. I am...or was, A Dark Lord's pawn. Unfortunately, beyond circumstances I couldn't control, which included Barius, I am now free-lance.
If you do not believe me, I'm sure you trust Kiyara. Or Barius. But that is irellevent: I wish to seek something that which you may hold a key to.``"

``Zhilia holds up the piece of paper, frowning, but he continues:

"`1I was not born... or created, per se, as a Mazoku. I am, or was, a Golden Dragon. And now, I am nothing more than a hybrid chimera. What I want from you goes double: please hear my story, and than hear my offer.
I was born as a proud, red-blooded, golden dragon, to two loving parents and a older sister. Or was it brother? But it doesn't matter. I was adventurous, and I, at the young human age of nine, decided to venture forth into the world.
What I found there was cold, and what I wanted just out of my reach. I had few friends and comrades, and even they were not true friends. Finally, weary, exhausted and frustrated, I decided to back home.

What I found was a demon army, lying on top of my village. Everyone I knew was dead, and my family gone...

Later, after my ressurection, I found out that one of the Dark Lords, under the control of Chaotic Blue, had specifically targeted me as a victim and as a subordinate. After years of hardships and humiliation, I finally buckled... I wasn't a dragon.
I was a Mazoku, play-thing of demonic demi gods. And later, I found out that the afore-mentioned massacre of my village was a test of my skill as a fighter. What happened thereafter is ancient history. I worked and slaved as a Mazoku.
Now, I am nothing more than a middle-class B demon with no Dark Lord to follow, or a Demon God to worship. And what I want dearly, is to remember what it was like. Before I was ressurected as a Mazoku. I want to remember my family.

Although this seems foolish and trivial compared to oh so many other things... like a cure for my Mazoku-ness. Or peace and goodwill toward all beings. But I am a humble demon. All I want is my memories before I was killed and ressurected.
I believe, as you being a priestess, you have some sort of way to do so. That is what I want. If you wish to take this seriously, please meet me another time. Alone. I will hear what you want from me than.
Oh, and this message has been written by special ink which only your eyes can read. Do not speak of this to anyone else. Do not show the note to anyone else, because it will look like a blank to them.``" 

Sincerely,
Zhilia Zoana

``Zhilia stands up, about to tack the message on the bulletin board, when he gets another idea:

"`1P.S.: Nice right hook mace-swing ya got there. It'd be a shame if you mace disappeared, ne?``"
~
