Subject Risking Life And Limb? Or.... Death To the Anti-Christ!~
Text
"You! Stop right there."
Zhilia went from full-stealth-i'm inconspicuous-so-dont-see-me mode to full-oh-shit mode. He watched frowning as four Mazoku guards walked up to him.
Sporting enough phallic symbols to make a mortal blind, these four wore what seemed to be full body armor. With almsot no head and a gigantic maw full of flashy white teeth, they advanced towards Zhilia with an air of arrogance.
"Alrighty than. Who're you, and whatcha doin' here?" one said in an Irish accent.
"I'm the neighborly, friendly elecritian! I'm here to fix your T.V."
"TV? Umm...Bart, what's a TV?"
"How should I Know? Ask the one with the Irish accent."
"CHEESE!"

As the four guards argued over what a 'TV' was, and what the one with the irish accent meant by 'cheese', Zhilia managed to slip in unnoticed. (But than, a polka-dotted elephant probably could have slipped in also)
Passing numerous torture chambers, prisons, pits 'o dooms, chains of dismemberment and a 'chamber of Barney's greatest hits', he finally reached what looked like a gigantic staricase.

"Oooookay. Here we go." Zhilia said, rubbing his hands together. "Either it's the HARD way, or the LONG way..."
Pretending that the theme from Mission Impossible was in the air, Zhilia quickly pulled out a briefcase from his sub-dimension. Setting it near the staircase, Zhilia squeezed his eyes shut and waited for a big explosion.

Of course, the briefcase being full of dog-chow, did not explode. Instead, the five-headed guard dog of abyss, doom, despair and what-not, did explode out ofthe secret hiding place in the staircase. While it was busy chowing down on Premium Pro-Dog 
Chow Bits and Licks, Zhilia proceded to float up the staitway.

"Lessee. If I remember correctly, the main chamber is aaaaaaaal the way at the top! And all the way through is a maze os horrendous, hideous and otherwise disgusting group of Mazoku that an probably rip my lungs out! I'll teleport."

After a quick jump to the Negaverse to say hello to Queen Beryl, than hopping to the nearest McDonalds (they were everywhere, even in the middle of a dimension gate) he quickly went back to the top of the tower.

"Hmm. Should I knock? Peek inside? Or rudely and chaotically blast it open, jump in guns blazing, and just HOPE that Sortes won't fry my ass? BONZAAAAI!"

No one was there. Zhilia acquired an old karate stance, folding his front leg up to his chest and waving his staff around like a bo. A quick hop, hop, cartwheel, and he landed on the main throne.

"Heeeey. This feels nice. No wonder she never let me on it." Zhilia sniggered, leaning back. "I hope she goes shopping for a long time."

"Oh, but I am here." a teenage girl, with blond hair, stepped out of the shadows by the massive door. She let the doors ominously close by themselves, making a nice 'CLICK' sound as the force field locks engaged itself.


To Be Continued....
~
