To      barius kiyara~
Subject Give me Liberty, or Give me Death! No, it's not a multiple choice answer!~
Text
"Now, now Zhilia. It's not nice to barge into a heavily fortified fort of solitude like that. You know how to knock." Sortes said slyly, leaning on a black candle-holder. With a flick of her wrist, Zhilia's staff flew from his hands and clattered to
the floor a few feet away. Zhilia gave Sortes his patented 'I-Know-Something-You-Have-No-Clue-That-You-Didnt-Know' look.

"It won't work this time Zhil. Your of no use to me, and I don't want to really argue with you anymore. If your here to conduct business...."
"Actually, I decided to see my poor, poor, old, senile mother. Because she decided to make a bad mistake, and, well, what with the honor of the family name in peril." Zhilia shrugged.

"You do know that, being subordinate-less, minion-less, right-hand-less, and whatever else you want to call it-less, your nothing more than a she-beast with power. You got no eye to guide you."

Sortes gave no, if any, reaction to his assessment. Instead, she levitated his staff into her hands, and examined the green emerald on top.
"Oh...oh...you kept the amulets." she perked up slightly. "I gave them to you, if you remember. As a fourth anniversary present. I was wondering whether you had kept them or not."

"They were very useful." Zhilia smirked. "And now, they will help me even further."
"Because, you see, I think we need to think this out. You have power: something you stole from me, and something I want. In me, you have information. Something YOU want."

"What? You wish to become by priest again? The answer is n--"
"No, no you idiot! I would rather kill myself than ally with you." Zhilia snorted, suddenly showing signs of irritation. "And neither do you, methinks."
"....I do want a subordinate. This dark place is lonely." Sortes finally sighed. "And I do need someone to watch over my army. They've been becoming less disciplined and lax ever since you left..."
"Yes, yes, i noticed. I managed to slip past four Galins without even being maimed. VERY lax security, Sortes. You should be ashamed."
"You do know I can kill you, right?" "Quite."

A dark silence fell on the two of them, before Zhilia broke it by pulling out a large brown table from his sub-dimension pocket. "Let's do business. We both got something we want, so let's be reasonable."

Sortes nodded silently, and sat down, her numerous bracelets clinking on the waxed table and her blonde hair flowing behind her softly.

-TBC-
~
Sender  Zhilia~
Date    Wed Jul 19 00:19:35 2000~
Stamp   963983975
To      barius kiyara~
Subject Note Number Three. PRetty bland huh?~
Text
Clink. Clink. Clink.

Zhilia smiled slowly, watching as Sortes annoyingly clicked her razr sharp nails on the waxed table, looking bored and frustrated.
This was just stupid. This was irritating. This was...

"Have any threes, Sortes?" "Go fish."

Zhilia happily plucked a card from the deck, and squealed in delight. "Yayay! Four threes!" he slapped the four on the table, noting with happiness Sortes looked very disgusted.
"This is stupid." Sortes finally said, saying her mind. "Why the hell are we playing cards?"
"Don't take out home in vain, Sortes." Zhilia admonished, spreading his cards out again. "And anyway, playing fun and entertaining games help the mind process! Your turn."

Squinting suspiciously at Zhilia, Sortes quickly sorted through her deck. "Umm...er...have you got any tens?"
"Nope. Go fish!"

Sortes sighed, and picked a card. A seven. Zhilia smiled happily, and plucked three cards from his hand. "Got any tens?"

Sortes did a sizable WHUMP sound as her head met the table in surprise. "WHAT?! You little cheater! I'm gonna fry your little fruity ass to Neo Tokyo and back, you little--"
"Temper, temper! I was just asking. Oh well. Got any sixes?" "Errr...." Sortes handed hi ma six-- upon which he laid down the four cards. Zhilia smiled thickly and innocently. "Your turn!"

"Do you have any kings?" Sortes asked, ruffling her cards in despair. Zhilia shook his head madly. "Nope! Go fish!" Flip. King. She had three kings!!!

"Do you have any kings?" Zhilia asked innocently--one card in his hand.

"All right, that's it! YOUR DEAD MEA--"
"I propose that the winnder of this bout get to choose their prize!" Zhilia smirked. "So whoever wins, gets to choose what the other person does!" and before Sortes could protest, he had plucked her three kings and aid them down. 

"......" Sortes wittily said. "..."
"And I propose..." Zhilia said, before letting Sortes recover. "That I get the philosopher's stone!!"

"Your dead meat." Sortes glowered... a blaskish glow on her eyes. "I've had enoguh of this foolishness long enough! You die now!!"

Zhilia produced out a black stone from his grown pouch--making Sortes stop and stare. "Not while I hold the stone. Wonder why you couldn't detect Barius? Let's just say... I borrowed those powers...see, this game was just to distract you."
"And now with me holding the stone, watcha gonna do...when the PSYCHOTIC little fruity BASTARDS on top of you?!" Zhilia giggled, grabbing his staff and swinging at Sortes. She stopped it with a flick of her finger, and let Zhilia fly.

TBC...
~
Sender  Zhilia~
