To      barius kiyara~
Subject Four. Just Four. IM BORED!!~
Text
Sortes quickly checked her mentalliy: you didn't become a Dark Lord from being stupid. And got...nothing. Zhilia had the stone. Zhilia had the upper-hand. And o top of that, he was acting freaky again.

"All right. Fine. You got what you wanted: I get something from you." Sortes said smugly, rubbing her hands together. "Give me Five questions."

Zhilia nodded. "Okey dokey. Where is Neo Tokyo located? How many mortals have been killed in the Great Mazokuian War of 1267? What happened to Jaki'Lasem the Great, one of Mortal's finest sorcerers? Why am I here? What's cheese?"

"....no. I meant, I ask, you answer." Sortes sneered in frustration. "don't play mind games with me!!" Nodnodnod. "Okay. Where is Barius?"
"On Earth, somewere. is my best guess."
"Where on Earth?"
"On the ground."
".....how'd you block my astral plane presence so you cansteal the stone?"
"It's a secret. ... ... ... What?!!! It's an answer, isn't it?!"
"Damn you. Umm. What is this power you were talking about?"
"She's a goddess from another dimension. She got lost."
"Now we're going somehwere. Where's this dimension of her?"
"That, too, is a secret! Well, that's five! Tata! I hope you rot in hell...wait, you do! Hee hee hee." Zhilia waved, and vansihed faintly before disappeaering altogether.




+++++++++

"Daddy?" a Farmer's Son looked up. "Looks like an earthquake and a storm brewing, daddy."
"That's right, son. Looks like a blighter. Better get inside."

++++++++

"AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAARRRRRRGGGG!!!!!" the four guards, still wondering what 'TV' meant, began the slow mental process of finding out what the big crash of glass meant...
