Text
`8-=Beep! Imcoming Transmission=-``

`#Sirus' face appears on the Comm-Link moniter.``

"`^Marhault... I recieved your last communication. Needless to say, I'm
worried. Your body is not becoming unstable, I hope. At any rate, please
remain focused on our missions.

First on the agenda is getting you back to the homeworld. There you will
be able to recieve some aide from the High Preist there. This is only if
you are willing to get any aide you can. However, things might be a bit on
the edgy side on the homeworld.

This brings me to the next item on itenerary. Fenris is gone. ...And to
top it off, the last Juraian Elder has just passed away. At the time, there
are no leaders present on the planet. I'm not sure what to do yet.

Hmm. Also, there are two wars brewing. One will be fought here... Against the
reformed MDS. The other will be a silent war over heaven. As you know, there
are no good Gods left. All represent evil and selfish behavior... This means
we will all be in trouble when the war over Heaven begins... Unless...``"

Sirus shakes his head and adjusts his shirt. "`^We need to ressurect someone.
This person is not a mortal... It is a deity. A powerful begin able to show
us the light. He is...The Serraph.``"

Sirus gets a seriou look and studies the moniter. "`^Marhault. This mission
is of the most serious type. You will remain silent of all I say. It is vital
that you tell no one of this. But... I am going to ressurect the Serraph. I
have already enlisted Thaais for this assignment. You will be her partner.``"

"`^Marhault. You will make an accension. I cannot tell you how or when, but
I have known for some time you have something brewing within you that will
lead to bigger and better things. Your mission is split.``"

"`^You will go to Jurai, or contact Thaais. Both of these are both of the
utmost importance, and also, of the top secrect protocol. Sirus out.``"

`8-=Transmission ended.=-``
