Sender  Zhilia~
Date    Tue Jul 25 00:26:36 2000~
Stamp   964502796
To      barius kiyara~
Subject Ressurection: Beginnings...~
Text
12:45. Midnight, Neo Tokyo Time. East of the Eastern Wall of Neo-Tokyo.

A man. A tall, hairy man. Not like a bum, mind you-- he slicks his hair with Gel of Aloe and shampoos it with Kee's Rose and Petal Shampoo of Slick Hair everyday. No, he had slick, 'Im-a-bad-ass' hairy look.
He wore a trench-coat, a new fad for people who wanted to seem inconspicuous and really wanted attention. Black trench-coat, black shirt, baggy black pants. A scabbard. An ordinary sword. Something almost completely unseen in today's technological w
orld.

He stood still for a moment. Than he cracked open a cigarette box, and lit one.

"Damn. Bastard. I'm gonna kill you someday." the Dark Lord vowed angrily, flicking away the recently lit cigarette, and hoping it would create a nationally dangerous forest fire.

1:47. Morning, Neo-Tokyo Time. East of the Eastern Wall of Neo-Tokyo.

Sirge glanced up momentarily as Zhilia teleported besides a dim night light, huffing and red in the face. Without a second thought, Sirge stood up as fast a a bullet and drove his sword through his body, until the hilt touched Zhilia's back.

"Nice...to...see ya...too! Dark Lord...Sirge." Zhilia gasped. "Mind un-sticking that outa there? I, uhh, just got a surgery. And I reaaaally hate washing my clothes..."
Sirge slid his sword out, and sneered. Red blood, along with black, splattered his sword and his trench-coat. "Mind telling me what's going on? You were one of Sortes' best subordinates. Why da hell'dya leave?"
"Well, that is a secret--"
"And why the HELL is Chaotic Blue suddenly so damn hush-hush?! Give me 'it's a secret' crap again, and i'll run you through againya, ya fruity bastard."

Zhilia pouted. "Really! Everyone keeps telling me, 'your a fruit' or 'your a real bastard'! Than they die. Do you think I WANT to be reminded?! Why, If I had SEVEN CENTS for each time someone called me---ERK!"
Sirge growled, and lifted Zhilia by the neck. "Tell me. NOW. Or else half of you might be living in underwater. The otherh alf might be halfway to the moon."

"Real poetic, Sirge! I'm touched." Zhilia sniffed. "I mean, what with all that potent, anger gathered up inside you... your a real artist! ... ... ... what's with that face?"
"Zhilia, you've never really faced death, have you?"
"No, but i've listen to Barney's Greatest Hits to make anyone wish to die...." Zhilia's words got cut off as Sirge head-butted him, than back-handed him. Zhilia went flying, and thudded hollowly against a brick wall.

"Zhil, really, let's make this short and simple. I mean, what good will it do to you IF YOUR HEAD IS NOT ATTACHED TO YOUR BODY?! So be a nice trickster priest, and tell me everything you know."
"Well, when I was about 1256 years old, Sortes told me I had a nice bum... and than, in the Great Mazoku War of 1264... or was it 1246? I killed off your General cause he was in my way..."
Sirge twitched. "....You're in DEEP SHIT ZHIL!! DIE!!"
"And than, there was that TIME when I noticed ya hitting on that golden dragon...." Zhilia grinned ferally. "Eh? Eh? Won't look good on your resume when Chaotic Blue boots ya for talkin' to the enemy, eh? I think a bit of blackmail is in order, no?"

"Won't help ya if your dead." Sirge growled, but he seemed to calm down some. "You little trickster....priest.....dammit. Fine. You.....wanted something."
"Indeedy I do. Gosh m'gosh b'gosh... I nearly forgot! How silly. Sirge, I want your damn army." "..."

TBC
~
