Subject Report of the war...~
Text
`8_-=*INCOMING TRANSMISSION*=-_``

`1Lord Sirus, Marhault..Ruka showed up yesterday.  Now, I managed to wound
her pretty bad, but apperantly after I -thought- she was killed, someone got her
back to MDS central...where she was healed at Laeris' direction by a few
other people.  But...thing is, Laeris -is- trying to stop things.
She apperantly tried to convince Ruka to leave Legis with her...Ruka
refused, of course.  But she showed up last night trying to get away
from Legis...after the fight with him, which I'll get into later.
But after we offered her a place to hide along with Werien, Ruka
and some other girl in an MDS uniform showed up and she went back
with them.  BUT- her plan is to force a heavily wounded Legis back
into his sword, which she'll carry with the Sonic Knight Blade she has.

Now, as for the battle with Legis.  He was rather unhappy about me trying to
off Ruka.  Well, I suppose -most- of the details are rather normal battle
stuff, but there were a couple of things that stood out.  One- Legis
was extremly wounded by some kind of Chi disc from Quillan.  I think 
thats why Laeris is going to have a chance to force him into the blade.
And..the other thing.  I got shot up pretty bad too...I would have
been killed, but...I..well, -somehow- blocked the last burst with some kind
energy field...Quillan said it was similar to his Talons...maybe you two
can tell me about it....thats it, for now...get back to me.

Angel``
~
Sender  Kiyara~
Date    Tue Jul 25 18:04:45 2000~
Stamp   964566285
To      barius, zhilia~
Subject Family??~
Text
Kiyara sighs as she looks out the baywindow of her bedroom.
'It's only a matter of time till he contacts me again.' She thought, as she stood, and walked out to the balcony.
'If he wants the StarSharD soul, he's gotta kill me first...I won't let him get it....' 
She idly ran her hand across the crumbling balcony railing, as she does, it returns to new.
"First Sortes, and now this......"
Kiyara looks back in at Barius, who is sleeping peacefully inside.
'If he new the seriousness of this, he wouldn't be sleeping so well...still, it may be a good thing he doesn' know..I won't endanger another life....
'Especially not his.' She thought grimly. She looked down at her arm, the layers of skin still growing back from when Khale had ordered his demons to slash her arm for a warning...it still ached.
A sudden deep voice chuckled and then spoke. "Did you like my present, Kiyara?"
"What do you think??" She growled at him. "Oh yes Khale. I love it when you rip open my flesh." Her voice dripping with sarcasm.
Khale chuckled and a hologram of a man in his early 40s with spikey black hair and beady little eyes appeared before her, dressed in pants, and shirt, and a cape trailing behind him.
Kiyara looked him over and frowned. "Why can't you just leave me alone?"
"Oh Kiyara, I could leave you alone....all you have to do is give m--"
Khale growled for a moment, before looking at Kiyara and snickering softly.
He sighed and leaned on the railing. "You look like your mother."
"Huh?? How do you know about her?"
Khale laughed again, a synical glint in his eye. "I  know more about her than you ever will..."
Kiyara watched him carefully as he grinned and looked at her. "Yes," he continued, "Such a shame I had to do away with her.....But she knew too much....As did you....and that's why you were sent away."
Kiyara gulped slightly "..."
"And now, a surprise for you..." Khale grinned and leaned closer. "Kiyara...."
"Have you ever wondered who your parents were?"
Kiyara blinked at him, not believeing what she thought he meant. "You can't be....."
Khale laughed mercilessly. "Yes, Kiyara, you're MY daughter."
"No....no...NO! You're NOT my father you BASTARD!" Kiyara screamed and ran inside. Khale laughed again before concentrating a small amount of his power and had the house black out, along with the backup generator.
He snickered a last time before disappearing into the dwindling night... 'I'll come again daughter...and when I do...beware...you'll be begging for mercy....One of you will go..you..your lover.....or your son....'
~
Sender  Zhilia~
Date    Tue Jul 25 18:37:46 2000~
Stamp   964568266
To      barius kiyara~
Subject Ressurection: Beginnings/2~
Text
"...you little idiot. You think you're psychically powerful enough to control five million lesser-demons? Out on the battle field, no less."
"Now, now Sirge. Let's think about this. If I WASN'T strong enough, would I be here, asking you, a Dark Lord, oh almighty one, for a little favor? Nah.
And anyway, we both come from the same gene pool. We both are loners. We both like doing it our way, or no way. You are Prince of War, right? War in unpredictable. Unpredictability is Risky. Risky is Chaotic. And I'm the Knight of Chaos. Got it?"

Sirge sighed heavily, and leaned against a wall. "I know how you operate. You make a deal. You intentionally create loopholes, in case you get caught with your boxers down. You cheat, scam, backstab. Why should I trust you with my army?"
"Because I'm your favorite fruity priest?" Zhilia smiled. Sirge gave him a hard, unemotional look. Zhilia frowned. "You need to lighten up, Sirge. You know, the only reason the other Dark Lords hate you is because your as socialable as a rock?"

".......what's in it for me." Sirge growled, his hands resting on his scabbard. Zhilia grinned. "Nothing much. Heh. I owe you a favor."
"Try looking for any loopholes in that." Zhilia continued. "I owe you a favor... short and simple. And in return, I get temporary control of your army, en facto, contracto, whenever i feel like i have a need for it."

"In essence, I give you the most pwoerful demonic army out there, and you're giving me a favor." Sirge intoned in a monotonous voice. "You think i'm some sort of newbie lesser-demon on crack, don't you?"
"Heck NO! I think of you as an old fogie anti-socialist with Mazoku Alzheimers Disease. See, I actually respect you." Zhilia grinned. "Unlike those other Dark Lords, you actually know what your doing. I mean it..."

Sirge gave Zhilia a stoney look, before nearly falling backwards, laughing heartily. "HaHAHAaHaAAAAA!! Oh, Zhil, you amaze me. You actually have the brains of a snail! Asking a Dark Lord for his army."
"Snail?" Zhilia said, frowning. "Nowaitaminute..."

"Okay, fine. I'll humor the Trickster Priest." Sirge grinned. "I wasn't gonna do anything with my army anyway. Chaotic Blue still won't talk to me after the Buttered Corn Incident. You can have it. At least they will stop whining for blood and gore.
"Thank you, Dark Lord Sirge Jukensi'les, Prince of War." Zhilia bowed respectively. "Don't worry, your army is in good hands. They'll have all the violence they'll want. Soon."

"What'cha gonna do, Zhil? Overrun Neo Tokyo?" Sirge laughed. "The mortals won't stand a chance in a freezing hell. And that reminds me. Did Vasx change his decor in hell yet, or is he still into the flame an fire look? He won't talk to me either."
"He's still into the boring flame an fire look. He has NO taste in decorating." Zhilia huffed. He bowed a second time, and teleported away.

2:23. Morning, Neo Tokyo Time. East of the Eastern Wall of Neo Tokyo.

"Zhil...don't be an idiot..be careful man." Sirge whispered, before shaking his head and disappearing...
~
Sender  Thaais~
Date    Wed Jul 26 20:58:42 2000~
Stamp   964663122
To      Ethera~
Subject A letter from mom...~
Text
``  As you walk into your bedroom for the night, you spy an envelope on your pillow.
You clearly see Angel's wide, looping handwriting on the envelope, your name written.
You open the envelope and pull out a few sheets of paper, revealing a letter.

``  `2Ethera, my daughter,

See, I told you I'd write.  You asked about Jurai, didn't you?  Well, Jurai...hm..
Jurai is the planet of my birth.  It's a ways away from the solar system...an absolutely
beautiful world...trees everywhere, very little violence...oh, I could go on and on
about it...I'll take you sometime, I promise.  Jurai has a clan on Earth, who
deal with the bad guys who attack..like Legis.  They defend those who cannot defend
themselves.  As for my relation to the clan on Earth, I'm relatively new...but..
well, I'm not that high on the toem pole there either, but I am part of the royal
bloodline.  So, guess what? Your momma's a princess.  Hm...I'm not sure what else
to include, ask Marhault or Sirus if you have any other specific questions.
Tell them I said for you to ask about it.

I do love you, very much.  Tell Marhault and Sirus not to be surprised when they
see me next, looking older and all.  Again, I love you sweety.  Ja ne!

Your mother,
Angel
``
~
Sender  Kiyara~
Date    Thu Jul 27 12:39:25 2000~
Stamp   964719565
To      Barius, Zhilia, Marhault~
Subject Death denied~
Text
The room was too bright and cheery for her to stay in any longer.
Even after the talk with Ryjaih that warned her to stay well away from Barius...she couldn't stay here any longer. There were too many memories that came back to her by simply staying on the same Satillite Barius once was in, and Ryjaih was still.
Kiyara thought back to her discussion with Ryjaih hours before.
"You can't go after him. Stay away from Barius." Ryjaih had said. But being the stuborn one she'd been,  Kiyara refused to take the advice. She knew she'd have to see him, even if he was just a puppet now...
"He's no longer Barius, child, he's the other now. Why do you think he tried to kill you?"
'I don't care.' Kiyara had answered. 'I can't live without at least seeing him.'
"He'll have his fun.."
She had figured out what that meant,  but asked anyway.

Kiyara stood up from the bed she'd been sleeping in, reliving her whole nightmare. `$I`'`m` `n`o`t` `s`t`a`y`i`n`g` `h`e`r`e` `a`n`y`m`o`r`e``....
`$I `$c`$a`$n`$'`$t `$s`$t`$a`$y `$h`$e`$r`$e `$a`$n`$y `$m`$o`$r`$e`$.``
Kiyara stood and walked out of the room, he sneakers silent on the floor, and took a disc from her pocket. She  placed it on her arm and pushed it down. 
In a multi-colored flash of light, she was gone, and back on earth, in Neo Tokyo, where Ryjaih had 'saved' her. 
Suddenly, she was in her backyard, the ground still covered in craters and the crevices that had sent the message to her before anything had happened.
In the same condition she'd seen before she left, were the letters `2D `2I `2E``. Kiyara looked around as the scenes flashed over and over through her mind.
She let tears fall as she looked at the ground and saw a dark stain on the grass...where Barius had been slain. IT played over and over again, the God raising his sword and plunging it down...
Kiyara floated up into the air, over the craters and crevices, and over to the bench she'd been crying in hours before any of this happened. She sat down, tears slowly running down her face.
"Barius...you promised everything would be alright....you promised...." 
She let herself cry for five minutes, then teleported herself inside her house. Everything inside looked perfectly fine...but in fact, nothing would be 'fine' for a long time.
She walked up the staircase, memories of running up and down it, running through the halls with laughter following were brought unwillingly back to Kiyara. She grimaced and forced herself not to cry.
Kiyara walked up another flight of stairs, to the bedroom she'd been in when everything had begun. She sadly walked over to the bed, and sat down, the water rippling under the covers.
Ryjaih had asked her if a sword was plunged through her stomach, would the baby live. 'yes.' She'd answered. `$U`$n`$t`$i`$l `$D`$e`$m`$m`$e`$t `$i`$s `$b`$o`$r`$n`$,`` she thought, `$w`$e`$'`$r`$e `$b`$o`$t`$h `$i`$m`$m`$o`$r`$t`$a`$l`$.`$.`$.`$.``
She reached down to the inside of her pant leg and took out a lon dagger. For a moment she examined it, not sure of where she'd put it...
Suddenly a pain shot up through her stomach. She smiled fondly and rubbed her stomach gently. "It's okay little one." She said softly. "I'll not harm you at all."
Her nightmare played for her once more. Everything rang through her mind. 'Kiy-kiyara.....ru..n....' 'Not without you!' 'Child! Get back here!' A deep laughter, and flash of light, and then Barius was dead.
She'd run back to him, and resurrected him, only to find out, that he was not Barius......but instead the God that had killed him. 
Kiyara blinked and looked around the room. She closed her eyes and remembered the last words she'd heard from what used to be Barius...
"You can't hide forever. I'll get you."

She took the dagger off the bed where she'd laid it down, and positioned it above her heart.
'A few last tears...' She thought. She cried for a fw minutes, remembering all the times BArius had comforted her, telling her they'd get through this together...
"I love you Barius..."
~
Sender  Kiyara~
Date    Thu Jul 27 12:48:53 2000~
Stamp   964720133
To      Barius, Zhilia, Marhault~
Subject death denied / continued...~
Text
She closed her eyes and gulped, before quickly bringing the dagger down into her heart.
There was a sickening thud, before she pulled out the dagger, which was covered in blood. Her eyes were shut tight, but even then tears managed to fall.
She dropped the dagger and shakily brought her hand to the wound in her chest. It had already begun to close up.
"Damn it......"
Kiyara cried again, saying back on the bed, her shirt covered in blood which soon stained the sheets.
Tears covered her vision and she closed her eyes. `$I `$h`$a`$t`$e `$m`$y `$l`$i`$f`$e `$s`$o `$m`$u`$c`$h`$.`$.`$.`$B`$a`$r`$i`$u`$s`$.`$.`$.`$I `$d`$o`$n`$'`$t `$w`$a`$n`$t `$t`$o `$l`$i`$v`$e `$w`$i`$t`$h`$o`$u`$t `$y`$o`$u`$.`$.`$.`$I `$c`$a`$n`
`$I `$c`$a`$n`$'`$t`$.`$.`$.``
"Why can't I die!?!?" She shouted. Frowning, she forced herself to black out of consciousness. Even then, her nightmare played over and over again...
~
