Stamp   967872113
To      Elg~
Subject `&T`7he `3A`#r`&riv`#a`3l``~
Text
`8Two years ago...``

``   The icy spears of rain came down upon the land, and the land became cold
and desolate. All the inhabitants of this sodden country took shelter amongst
the crowded apartment buildings and towering skyscrapers. There was no sound
but that of rain drops hitting the rooftops and ground. Out beyond the concrete
jungle, far after the road ends, down in the dirt and grass, a figure has
scarred the earth where he had set his feet down for the first time. His body
lays unmoving in the dirt, beaten harshly through its travel.

``   He awakes, confused and torn. Unable to understand the surrounds or piece
together his mind. Everything is gone. Nothing can be recalled. Even his name
is lost. He sees his hands, bloody and shredded. Everything hurts, down to the
smallest bone. He looks to the only light shining through the darkness of night,
a city illuminated by neon signs and glowing towers of steel. The battered spirit
holds on to his shattered body as he makes his way for Neo-Tokyo.

`&To be continued...``
~
Sender  Tyronos~
Date    Sat Sep  2 00:29:12 2000~
Stamp   967872552
To      Elg~
Subject `&T`7he `3A`#r`&riv`#a`3l `8- `&P`7art `&2``~
Text
``   `6"`^So, let's have a look at you, shall we?`6"`` The doctor inquired as he inspected
``   The doctor wore a large lab-coat, which was as about as white as his hair and 
mustache. He peered down at the armor I wore through his seemingly huge glasses.
The doctor unraveled the bloodied rags I had wrapped my battered arms in.
``   `6"`^Hmm? What's this?`6"`` The doctor leaned over and studied my hand. `6"`^ACH! Cyber-
netic implantation. But this is strange... I've never seen these type of implants
before. They look ancient, and what are these?... Interesting.`6"`` He studied the
glittering steel under my skin for some time until he sat up and wrapped them up
again. `6"`^Here's some fresh bandages for you... OH, by the by, I'm Doctor Zaikahn,
Emilios Zaikahn. What is your name?`6"``
``   I thought for a long while, trying to dig up an answer to this doctor's question 
that I didn't even understand. `6"`^Trnnohss...`6"`` I suddenly sputtered out, unconsciously.
``   `6"`^Tyronos? Hmm, funny name. Well, you come back soon and we can fix those arms
of yours, ach ya?`6"`` I simply stared at him as he rolled this strange language at me,
`6"`^Gut! Now off you go.`6"`` He pushed me out of his office and went back to work.
``   I would come back often, only knowing the hospital as a reference point in such 
a big city. I eventually got the hang of the doctor's strange language he called 
`^"`6Inglissh`^"`` and finally began to understand the world around me. But the world
that I came from, would be a whole new mystery.

`&To be continued...``
~
Sender  Tyronos~
Date    Sat Sep  2 00:34:30 2000~
Stamp   967872870
To      Elg~
Subject `&T`7he `5V`%i`5sion``~
Text
``   I was walking down one of the many narrow streets that I used to live during
those dark days of confusion and terror before I met Dr. Zaikahn, when I was overcome
by the most terrible headache. I'd had no knowledge of what a headache was like
until now. A deep, sharp pain drilled into my head, probing every definition of pain
that could be cited. I felt hot, like I was on fire. Or rather, everything else was
on fire! I looked all around and the entire street was engulfed in flames, no inch
of ground escaped it's tyrannical wrath. I tried to run, but the heat pushed me back.
``   That's when I heard it. The most terrible sound I have ever heard. Screams. Loud,
shrieking screams of pain and sorrow. Children wailed and women screamed out to them.
The sound of pain filled my ears until I could not stand it! I covered my ears, but
it could not drown them out! Everything began to blur together, I saw many forms
moving about, running away from the flames in horrific terror. I screamed, `6"`^Fire!`6"``
and tried to help the blurry forms to escape, but before I could take another step,
I fell flat on my face.
``   And as quickly as they had arrived, the fire was gone. The screams no longer
filled the air, and the fearful masses were no where to be seen. I felt my forehead
and it burned as hot as the flames I saw. 
``   Standing upright again, I adjusted my headband and straightened my clothes. I
knew what a headache was, and from what I heard, you do not see an inferno filled
with screaming people. I tried to shake the feeling of helplessness and walked on.
Never have I been so afraid.
~
Sender  Tyronos~
Date    Sat Sep  2 00:39:49 2000~
Stamp   967873189
To      Elg~
Subject `1F`!a`#ll`!e`1n `8S`7t`&a`7r`8s``~
Text
``   Night enveloped the city of Neo-Tokyo, and all became dark. Only the illumines
lights of its buildings and streets could be seen in the blackness. Deep within
it's streets, a man rested his troubled mind. Even in his dreams he could rarely
escape dark visions of a past that he cannot grasp. Tonight however, he dreamed
nothing but the deep, calming silence of darkness. Tonight he can rest.

``   The stars shined a pale blue over the mountains. The moon's rays poured deep 
into the crevices of the countryside, giving a melancholy light to those who need
it most. Two deep red stars shined brightly in the sky, side by side. They danced
across the heavens with a dangerous grace, spinning slightly through the veil of
shadow on the hills. A deep stench of death filled the air and covered the land
to its deepest reaches. The man who sleeps in the city is oblivious to what deep
evil has befallen him and the city which he takes shelter. The flames of death
have once again been renewed.

`&To be continued...``
~
Sender  Tyronos~
Date    Sat Sep  2 00:49:42 2000~
Stamp   967873782
To      Elg~
Subject `1F`!a`#ll`!e`1n `8S`7t`&a`7r`8s `&P``art `&2 `8- `&T``he `1K`!i`1lling``~
Text
`8At the local bar...``

``   Tyronos puffed lightly on his cigarette as he reached into his jacket for the
local newspaper that he nabbed earlier.
``   `6"`^I'm so sorry, lemme get that,`6"`` Cyanne said, wiping up some wine that had been
spilled by a distracted customer.
``   Tyronos opened up his copy of the Tokyo-Times and read intently.

``                      `&Four Dead, Police Baffled``

``   He read at the top of the page. He read on, and began to mumble. `6"`^The hell...`6"``
``   `6"`^What's up?`6"`` Cyanne asked, coming back with a dirty rag.
``   `6"`^Four murders, slashed to death. All suffering from third degree burns all this
week`6"`` Tyronos replied, still reading.
``   `6"`^Jeez, any suspects?`6"`` Cyanne grimaced.
``   `6"`^Witness saw the killer fleeing from one of the crimes, said the killer was short,
and...`6"`` Tyronos paused, frozen in a stare at the article.
``   `6"`^And...?`6"`` Cyanne broke Tyronos' trance.
``   `6"`^Had... Had a tattoo on the forehead. Red dot encompassed by a circle.`6"``
``   `6"`^Weird...`6"`` Cyanne threw away the wine-drenched rag. `6"`^What's the world coming to?`6"``
``   `6"`^Really...`6"`` Tyronos stared off into space, thinking about the tattoo.

``   Images flashed in his mind, of the flames, the screaming. And more importantly...
The blood. It had been a while since the first hallucination, and it had only gotten
worse. Each time the sounds and images would get more distinct, getting more frightening
every incident. Tyronos would even see them in his dreams, people standing before the
flames, laughing. Sometimes holding conversation with him, in some sort of odd dialect.
He would see rivers of blood pouring down streets of small villages, houses burning to
the ground. The most memorable of all the images he would see in these terrible visions,
was what one of the forms had on his forehead. A tattoo. Red. And he was laughing at all
the destruction around him. Enjoying every minute of the inferno. Now the newspaper was
telling of a murderer with the same mark... Somehow, Tyronos knew, he was going to cross
paths with this mysterious person.

`&To be continued...``
~
Sender  Tyronos~
Date    Sat Sep  2 01:00:40 2000~
Stamp   967874440
To      Elg~
Subject `1F`!a`#ll`!e`1n `8S`7t`&a`7r`8s `&P``art `&3 `8- `&T``he `8D`7a`8rk `5S`%t`7r`&an`7g`%e`5r``~
Text
`8Down Wall Road...

``   It had been about an hour since Tyronos left the bar, still thinking about the murders
and that tattoo. Every time he thought about it, he had to adjust his headband, making
sure it was on right. As he was doing just that, he bumped into a fairly stocky man in a
hooded cloak.

``   `6"`^Sorry!`6"`` Tyronos apologized to the figure, and began to walk on.

``   `6"`^Gummo, ino de Trihnoss.`6"`` The figure turned and spoke after him.

``   `6"`^Excuse me?`6"`` Tyronos said back, unsure if the man said what he thought he said.

``   `6"`^Azo mi contoh, Trihnoss`6"`` The figure said, approaching Tyronos.

``   `6"`^I'm sorry, I don't understand.`6"`` Tyronos tried to see the man's face, but the hood hung
down and casted a shadow over the man's features.

``   The man simply paused and looked distressed at what Tyronos had said. Tyronos apologized
again for the bump, and began to walk off again. Just as before, the figure approached him
and began to speak.

``   `6"`^Keeoh no mi, Trihnoss.`6"`` The hooded figure said, making motions like he Tyronos knew him.

``   `6"`^I'm really sorry, but I don't remember you, or understand what you're saying.`6"`` Tyronos
told the man, but for some reason, could slightly understand the stranger's language. Deep
in Tyronos' mind, he could hear the screams of the from the inferno. Hurriedly, Tyronos ran
off, leaving the man to stand alone, calling back to him.

``   `6"`^Contoh ha, Trihnoss! TRIHNOSS!`6"`` The stranger yelled.

`&To be continued...``
~
Sender  Bryson~
Date    Sat Sep  2 01:05:15 2000~
Stamp   967874715
To      Lakavia~
Subject Takeda.~
Text
May 2nd - 6:30am... an unusual steadiness in the air..with the tranquil breeze... calm, serene ocean... 
almost seems too perfect.... but i know they are coming... to hunt us down? or to be hunted? that fate 
has yet to be decided... 

9:00am... a suttle quiver settles throughout my entire body... my heart beat fastens... 4... No, 5 of 
'em appear on the radar... the uneasiness gradually becomes more distracting as the distance between 
us... doesn't decrease...

9:15am... our one specific order is NOT to engage in combat unless fired upon.. my mind repeats this 
again & again... but we have them on the run... & are quickly closing in...

Base Control: "Bug Out!" "Return home!" " Do NOT engage!"

Wing2-3-4-5: "10-4...returning back to base"

9:20am... i know i should follow the order... but the urge is too strong.. im trying to fight it.. 
no use... my fingers slowly grip to the contours of the throttle... raising the thrust ever so 
slowly... then more rapidly... until i was unable to push any further... 
10 miles...9...8...7...6...5...4... i watch as they fade into existence over the horizon... 

9:30am... 

Base Control: "Wing1 you are ordered to turn around" "Do NOT engage in combat! Do you copy?"

i gave no response...... 3...2 miles..... a noise jolts me back... 0 *Beeeeeeep*... 
i can feel my thumb shift upwards... ready to press... i close my eyes and count... 3-2-1... 
"Fox1!" the missle breaks free from its brackets... 
again..."Fox2!"..."Fox3!"... the more i killed... the more i wanted to kill... 

9:32am... i see the missles tear through their targets... several massive explosions shoot 
past me... my hands tookover acted uncontrollably as the rest are showered in a spray of heavy 
machine gun fire... they too, share the same fate... 

9:45am... the U.S.S. Plathos comes into view... the thought of taking out the carrier 
crossed my mind several times... i begin a diving sequence as engine thrust increases... i 
take one last look as i grab the canopy hatch to release myself.......

Years Later...

Target 0 *Beeeeeeep*...."Fox1!..Fox2!..Fox3!" *slow & unsteadily* These sounds/voices... 
They replay..over & over.. the mental images haunt me... it's all i think about... the brutality.. 
the bloodshed.. the.. *pause* ... killing..... k-a-m-a-k-a-z-e... *nods* i like that... a good 
idea no? well i thought so....

These visions WERE reality... as a matter of fact they use to happen quite frequently... but 
the most recent came in the 1980's... conflict on the Mediterranian between us... & the Russians... 
I, Aaron Takeda... trained as an elite fighter pilot in the Navy's prestigious Weapons School.. was 
taught the arts of dog fighting & tactics for 5 years... i was among the best of the best.. not a 
finer class of military pilots exsisted... 5 of us.. me, the youngest at 24... i ruled the skies.. 
nations feared my presense... most opposed me not only as an American pilot... but as a civilian as 
well.. my mother was English, but my father was well..*silence*.. brought over on an illegal smuggling 
operation from Japan... some still had powerful emotions about this, who took it upon themselves to 
take it out on me... "To Serve & Protect My Country"... the 6 words i abided from since day 1... i 
shot to kill... noone got in my way... 

i was born the fight.. to finish the job...*pause*... i promised myself death... *shakes his head*... 
it was never suppose to end like this.....
~
Sender  Tyronos~
Date    Sat Sep  2 01:24:37 2000~
Stamp   967875877
To      Elg~
Subject `1F`!a`#ll`!e`1n `8S`7t`&a`7r`8s `&P``art `&4 `8- `&T`7he `2S`@e`&rpe`@n`2t `#A`3ppears``~
Text
`8Deep within the city's reaches...``

``   Tyronos' boots made a light clacking sound on the hard concrete as he strolled 
back home from another round at the grocery. It had now been at least month since 
he had first heard of the murders, and there were seven new victim's since. 
The city-wide manhunt had turned the town more paranoid and fearful than before.
But, things seemed to had subside... The killer's routine of 2 victims a week wound
gruesome crimes, it still did not know who the killer was. Neither did Tyronos. 
The visions of fire and slaughter increased night by night, as always, becoming
more frightening than the one before. Tyronos was, at first, afraid that they were visions
of the future, but the scenery of a seemingly medieval village somewhat eased him.
But now the question was, why did he see them? And why is it that the same murderer
in his dreams was stalking Tokyo as he questioned himself this?

``   Tyronos bent his head down, watching his feet walking, step by step, across the 
damp pavement. He gazed at the round, white, illuminations of the lamps and neon
signs off of the ground, watching the shadows cast across them and roll off.
Soon the lights dimmed and yielded to a large shadow, hovering directly above Tyronos.

``   Tyronos looked up and saw a figure sitting atop a building, its legs dangling off
the side casually.
``   `5"`%Well, well, long time no see.`5"`` The shadowed figure said, sounding quite deep,
obviously a large male.
``   `6"`^... Excuse me?`6"`` Tyronos finally said after a long pause of trying to make out
the man's features.
``   `5"`%Don't you recognize me? ... Perhaps if I came closer it would help...`5"`` The man
vaulted off of the rooftop and landed quite gracefully before Tyronos. `5"`%NOW do you
recognize me?`5"``
``   Tyronos looked hard through the dim light at the man, then suddenly got a picture.
Red. Blood red. And flames. The glowing red ring and dot stood out from the man's
forehead like a screaming demon trying to leap out of hell.
``   `6"`^Y-y-you're...`6"`` Tyronos dropped his things and stepped back. 
``   The man looked worried at this, and finally spoke, `5"`%I see... So it's true then..`5"``
``   Tyronos paused, stunned by the fact that a cold blooded killer stood before him.
Then sputtered, `6"`^W-w-what is?`6"``
``   `5"`%I heard those rumors about you, Trinohss, I see they're true.`5"``
``   Tyronos slowly began to sweat, `6"`^You must be mistaken. My name isn't Trinohss.`6"``
``   The man looked at Tyronos' headband, then moved his eyes to Tyronos' face, `5"`%Oh,
I know exacltly who you are. YOU'RE the one who is mistaken.`5"``

`&To be continued...``
~
Sender  Tyronos~
Date    Sat Sep  2 01:38:13 2000~
Stamp   967876693
To      Elg~
Subject `1F`!a`#ll`!e`1n `8S`7t`&a`7r`8s `&P``art `&4 `8- `&T``he `2S`@e`&rpe`@n`2t `#A`3ppears``, `&cont.``~
Text
``   `6"`^What?`6"`` Tyronos questioned the man, `6"`^W-what do you mean?`6"``
``   `5"`%You've forgotten... How pathetic.`5"`` The man sneered, `5"`%I would have expected 
more out of you. Such a strong warrior taken down... Not even in battle either.`5"``
``   `6"`^Warrior? I'm no warrior, I'm just--`6"``
``   `5"`%YOU'RE JUST A TRAITOR!`5"`` The man screamed, `5"`%The great Trinohss, taken in by 
mere mortals... If you were half the man you used to be, you would have turned this
city into ashes by now.`5"``
``   Tyronos could not understand a single piece of what this man was saying. This 
ruthless killer claimed he knew Tyronos, but did not look like anyone he had met,
`6"`^Half the man I used to be? What man did I use to be?`6"``
``   The man sighed, shook his head, then finally asked, `5"`%Do you remember how you got here?`5"``
``   Tyronos became puzzled, looked all about him as if the man were talking to someone 
else, then answered. `6"`^Um... I walked.`6"``
``   This angered the man, and he retorted, `5"`%Not here, here, you idiot. I mean how did 
you get HERE, in this city. Do you remember how you got to this city?`5"``
``   `6"`^I've always been here.`6"``
``   `5"`%Nonsense. How long have you been here? What was the last thing you remember?`5"`` The man 
asked.
``   Tyronos pondered, unsure what the man meant. After some thought he finally said, 
`6"`^I woke up in an abandoned apartment building near downtown about 2 years ago, beyond 
that...`6"``

``   The man made sort of an angry frown at Tyronos' saying, `5"`%Such a waste...`5"``
``   Tyronos gulped and spit out, `6"`^Who are you anyway?`6"``
``   The man turned, and spoke over his shoulder, `5"`%My name need not matters now. For the 
length of time that you'll live, you won't need to know anyone's name...`5"`` And with that, 
he disappeared into the shadows as quickly as he had appeared.

`@(`2OOC: From this point forward, Tyronos mysteriously disappears from the city to take shelter in the woods
for several months.  I.E. I left the mud because of stupid people.  You're not one of them, of course. ^_^`@)``
~
