Sender  Adapa~
Date    Mon Nov  6 20:45:24 2000~
Stamp   973565124
To      Sirus~
Subject `4Q`$u`^e`$s`4t`$:`8 The Show of Adapa's Budo; A Fight With Destiny``~
Text
`8   The burning city surrounded the final duo, forming a kind of cruel prison to trap them until their 
fates got the best of them. Dead bodies lie everywhere, cracked swords and smashed projectile 
weaponry scattered amongst this newly created Necropolis. The two glared each other down, one man had
waited, and the other traveled a great trek to encounter him.
`8   The man with long flowing white hair finally spoke, `^"`6Trihnoss... You... YOU BASTARD! I've waited a 
long, long time for this,`^"`8 The man trembled with pure hate and enmity for his opponent. The man in 
white armor and a black soul made a wide, wicked smile.
`^   "`6So... The valiant fighter of freedom, the slayer of beasts, the hero of the people, Adapa; now 
wants to die. How nice,`^"`8 Trihnoss chuckled darkly, `^"`6I suppose there's no need to introduce myself, 
since you already seem to know me.`^"`8 Adapa continued his steady glare, `^"`6You killed my brothers... How 
could I forget your ugly face?`^"``
`8   Trihnoss simply smiled, and waited. Adapa took no time at all and unsheathed his blade, halfway on
his screaming death-charge. Trihnoss thrust up his blade, bringing it forth halfway to block Adapa's 
swing. The blades sung a violent tune as they ground against one another. Trihnoss threw Adapa 
completely off balance with this, and cut through his midsection, his long-sword causing a mighty
disruption in the air as it passed harmlessly in nothing but air.``
`8   Trihnoss turned his attention skyward, where Adapa had escaped. The warrior plummeted to the 
earth, cutting his sword in a wide, downward arc. His Xokaian rival barely managed to roll away, 
getting rained on by rock and debris caused by Adapa's sword striking the ground. When Adapa looked 
up to see where Trihnoss was, he disappeared.``

`8   Quakes rocked the capitol, making notice of the two warriors' duel. More rubble and ruin had 
appeared due to the events. Flames shot toward the heavens, giant boulders were flung great distances,
and towering statues crumbled to the ground, becoming nothing more than gravel. Far off in the 
the eastern quarter of the city, another house exploded.

`8   Trihnoss heard a click. He spun around and opened his palm, fingers splayed. A grand sphere of 
yellow and red screamed into the alleyway... Moments later, flames shot up from the dead end of the 
street and smoke billowed out from between the two buildings.``
`8   Trihnoss waited, his hand still in the position it was in after the fireball. It only took a 
thousandth of a second between the tingling of hairs on the back of his neck, and quick footwork to 
fling Trihnoss backwards. The column that he was standing next to splintered and ruptured into 
millions of little marble-stone projectiles.
`^   "`6Not bad...`^"`8 Adapa remarked as he stepped from the shadows, standing on one floor of a gutted 
tower. Trihnoss spat, `^"`6You'll have to do better than that, mortal.`^"``
`8   Adapa somersaulted off the ledge and landed gracefully in the dust in a kneeling position. With 
one fluid movement, he pushed off the ground with one foot and thrust the other in front of his body 
to create enough momentum for his mind-splitting charge. The parry came, and he received a fist to 
the jaw. The young warrior stumbled back, but that didn't stop his determination in his current 
flurry of attacks. The thrust was parried; his reverse-cut didn't connect well, either. Adapa pushed 
the Xokaian's sword to keep it from piercing his midsection. Trihnoss kicked him in the back of the 
knee, forcing the warrior to the ground. He brought up his long-sword and cut down to split the man's 
skull open. Adapa's sword was flung across the road and lodged itself into the wood of a door.``


`8[`7Continued on Page 2`8]``
~
Sender  Adapa~
Date    Mon Nov  6 20:52:01 2000~
Stamp   973565521
To      Sirus~
Subject `4Q`$u`&e`$s`4t`$: `8The Show of Adapa's Budo; A Fight With Destiny, cont.``~
Text
`8   Trihnoss gaped at his opponent, who now had the Xokaian's blade between his palms. Blood flowed 
from Adapa's palms and trickled down his wrist. He brought up his foot and kicked Trihnoss' hilt, 
which was then followed by a heel to the gut.
`8   Trihnoss and Adapa both went down to the ground. The warrior scrambled through the dirt to get to 
his blade. Unfortunately, the Xokaian was already on his feet and had a large shard from the 
splintered column. Trihnoss slammed the marble onto Adapa's shoulder blade. Adapa rolled onto his 
back and blocked the second attack with his sword. He winced at the sharp pain that was creeping from 
his shoulder to his lower back. The rock was thrown into the air and shattered on the street. Adapa 
got to his feet as Trihnoss picked up his sword.
`8   The Xokaian screamed and cut at Adapa with attack after attack, each deflected by the warrior's 
nimble blade. On the fifth strike, Adapa blocked the chop, slid his blade along the Xokaian's so it 
threw its owner off balance. Adapa brought back his brand, gathering up all the energy he had left in 
his bones.
`8   The wind roared and rippled under the force of Adapa's swing. Trihnoss managed to spin his sword 
around to deflect the attack, but it only shattered...
`8   The Xokaian hit the ground, the blood flooded over his vision. Adapa panted and walked over to the 
fallen beast. He glared down upon Trihnoss' torn body, which was now very near death. Adapa brought 
up his blade to end this pathetic beast's life.
`8   Hate flowed into Adapa's mind, seeing the death and destruction caused by the helpless Xokaian 
that was before him. He gripped the hilt, feeling the fine threads spun about its wood casing for the 
metal beneath.
`8   Suddenly, like a rush of warm water over his eyes, Adapa saw it. Visions, images... Seeing past 
memories of old. Seeing memories a father and his son playing amongst the tall grass on a warm 
summer's eve. The old man's smile, his vibrant laugh and reassuring words... That warm heart.

`8   The sword clattered to the ground. Adapa looked at his empty hands, and to his fallen father.``


`6T H E  E N D``
~
Sender  Ruka~
Date    Fri Nov 24 14:41:50 2000~
Stamp   975098510
To      sirus~
Subject Battle~
Text
I crouch on the rooftop, looking down at the mess of humanity below. A scream rings out
as someone is extracted from one of the wrecked vehicles. One of the medics slips on the
mixture of blood and oil that greases the street and bites back a curse as he regains his
balance.
A black form ghosts past a doorway across the street, indistinct except for two red pin-
pricks of eyes. Darkness hides him; it is night and someone has shot out every street
light on the block.
-`1No witnesses, Ruka``- Salamander's voice curls warmly in my mind.
-`1No witnesses``- I agree, still looking down at the tangle of cars. My eyes wander over
the rainbow sheen of gasoline and oil on the street and I grin. A quick flare of fire in
my hand and a match drops like a falling star. The scene disappears in a conglomeration
of flame. There will be no witnesses.
I ignore the agonised cries of the humans below and turn away, not interested in the
sight of the burning, I have seen it far too often for it to hold any sort of value to
me. Turning away, I walk back over the rooftop the way I came, and climb over the lip of
the roof on the opposite side. I allow myself to drop to the ground. No amount of caution
can mask the sound of metal shod boots hitting pavement, and I freeze at the bottom, na-
rrowing my eyes to mask the distinctive red glow. I do not hear anything but the crackle
of fire and my own breathing and heartbeat, but still I am uneasy. The screams behind me
have already faded as fire steals voices of those that saw too much.
-`1Something is amiss.``-
-`1Is it? I was wondering if I was beginning to jump at nothing``-
-`1No, the scent of the area is all wrong, like dust and old death...``-
Salamander's comment is all the warning I get, not even my keen ears can hear the shadow
detatch itself from an alcove behind me. A cold blade lays itself across my neck, a whis-
per of voice and breath with no heat brushes against my ear.
'`2Don't move, little miss...``' hisses the voice behind me. A reflexive jerk slams my
elbow into the stranger's gut, but no breath rushes out with the blow, and the knife re-
mains rock steady, biting into my neck and sending a trickle of blood to soak my black
collar. Salamander's voice mutters a shocked expletive in the back of my mind and I still,
catching in a sharp breath, and miming a shiver, careful acting, maybe he'll think I am
scared. I feel Salamander's warm presence nearing.
"`1Wh..what do you want?``" I whisper, making my voice high and breathy. I don't have to
fake the shudder of revulsion as a dry tongue snakes its way to replace the knife point
that lowers to prick my side as the dribble of blood is lapped away.
Salamander's paws pad up the alley, I can hear them distinctly. -`1You are a dog. Sal.``- He'll
know what I mean...
Salamander walks up blatantly, his eyes shut, masking the glow. He can see what I see.
My assailant sees nothing but a stray dog, digging in the trash, and he is destracted by
the strange mix that is my blood in his mouth. Soon, Salamander is discounted as being
nothing important, and the vampire holding me directs his attention back to where I want
it. I am frozen in "terror" until a growl and a sudden leap yanks the creature away from
me. A spin and a kick to the chin snaps the thing's neck with a strangely dry crack, and
Salamander's bite pulls it to the ground. Quick work to behead it before it recovers.
The wound has already stopped bleeding. I leave the trash in the street to disintegrate
come morning and ruffle the fur on my familiar's head. We walk out of the alley together.

Team work, it makes life so much easier.

`8[`3MDS`8]`` Ruka Demaris `8[`3MD`#-`3124`8]``
~
