Subject Lone in the Woods...~
Text
`8(OOC: Since Seltain told Maiser to do this, this is what she would find.)``

``   Far into the depths of the Dareeata, in a green field by the river is a place where few visit or speak of.
There's a circle of trees which allow only a tiny bit of light to shine down into the center. This place was
once used for joyful occaisons, but now is a lone, hallowed place where souls only pass by in memory.

``   As you approach this place, two black-clad men glance back at you and quickly make haste to run away.
they soon disappear into nothingness.
``   But at the center of the circle is a stone, once made of white granite now deepened into a dim grey, and
vines clamber up its base. The stone, upon closer inspection, is actually a gravesite. The stone reads, etched:

``                     Rest In Peace,
``                Seltain Yasunori Keinehlt
``                       Died Age 4
``        "That who came with life, ended with life. 
``            And such is the way it should be."
~
