Subject I'd get fried if Brian wasn't Brian.~
Text
Seitzer spirals through wierd, squirly beams of light, with an abyss of 
nothingness, 360x360x360 degress.

Seitzer: "Didn't they use this in Chrono Trigger?  ...it looks like the void
in a way, but I'll be damned if I'm going back there."

He rockets along, devoid of gravity, with no sight of anything, the 
background never getting closer, and no foreground to speak of.  Finally,
(Yeah, I know you don't like this dramatic, descriptive crap) he reaches the 
end of his flight.. journey... slide... whatever...
---------------
Brian sits there, whapping away...

Brian: "Yeah, Pikachu... yeah.. this 'masturbation' thing is great, I wish
someone told me about it sooner!  Yeah... Pikachu, pika... chuuUUUUU!  It's
coming... IT'S COMING... IT'S--!"

Seitzer flies out the monitor, flying into Desh, both of them crashing into 
the wall.  A voice comes from the other side of a piece of the wall, covered
in cheesy posters.  Judging by how there was a knob sticking out it, it was
probably a door.

Voice: "Brian honey, I know you're... excited about you're new 'discovery',
and it's normal and all boys do it at your age and everything, but I think
you're taking it a bit far, what was that noise?"

Brian stumbles, trying to stand with his pants around his ankles.

Brian: "Shu-shut up, Mom!"

Mom: "You want a hug?  Animal cookies?  Chocolate chip?"

Brian: "NO!  Just go away!"

Mom: "Ok!  Sweet innocence, bud of my love!"

Seitzer: "Aww hell no..."

Seitzer brushes himself off, and goes to stand up, before slipping and 
falling again.  He sits up and looks at the bottom of his boot, seeing a 
white spooge.

Seitzer: "AWW HELL NO..."

Seitzer looks around, seeing a skinny white kid struggling to put his pants 
on, with wristbands and a sweatband, with pokemon and cheesy chick posters 
on the walls, and tennis crap everywhere.

SEITZER: "AWW HELL NO!"

Brian: "Wh--who are you!?  Are you the poke-master!?  Am, am I the chosen 
one!?  I CAN'T BELIEVE IT, I KNEW IT'D--"

Seitzer promptly plants his spoogafied foot in Brian's stomach.

Seitzer: "Shut up, you little idiot!  Put two and two together, I'm SEITZER! 
and I can't BELIEVE my luck!"  *tries to find a way back into the computer 
like a cat scratching at the door*

Brian: "OwwWWW!  Aahhh.. *gasp, heave*  You, WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE!"

Brian runs at Seitzer, who pops him in the forehead like he was knocking on
a door, and Brian falls over.
a door, and Brian falls over.

Brian: "Aah!  This, this is STUPID!  I should be able to KICK YOUR BUTT, I'm
a big boy now!" *points to the white stain on his shirt*  SEE!?  I SHAVE! 
YOU BETTER WATCH OUT, I'M A BIG KID TOO NOW!"

Seitzer: "..."

Without wasting speech, Seitzer grabs Brian's hair, and drags him out of the 
house, walking by Brian's confused mother.  On their way, they pass a young
girl, sitting in the kitchen.  Seitzer stops, and picks up Brian's head.

Seitzer: "Is that your step-sister?"

Brian: "OWWWW!  Nuh... NO!"

Seitzer walks up to her, holds her face and gives her a nice, big kiss, 
before walking out the door.  (Don't wanna get TOO obscene in an RP note)

Brian's step-sister: "Who *WAS* that MAY-AN!"
------------------------
Seitzer walks down the road, with Brian.

Brian: "STOP!  Suh, STOP IT!  WHERE ARE YOU TAKING ME!"

Seitzer: "Shut up, Brian.  Aah!  There!"

Seitzer walks up to the perfect trash can.  Aluminium, circular...
beautiful.  He jacks it and walks to the nearest street hill, shoves it on 
Brian's head, the excess garbage already in there keeping Brian snug, and 
pushes him down the hill.

Brian slides until the can eventually turns horizontal, and he starts 
rolling all the way down, into a traffic intersection, getting hit by a 
steam roller and dying painfully, with no honor, and soiled pants.

Seitzer: "At least he got to jack off first.  Now... back to his sister."

TO BE CONTINUED
P.S, I see my editing error, but I'm not re-writing the entire note.
~
