Subject The Cat's Meow, Kyanii's Origin~
Text
Hurrying to school one again late as ever, Kyanii wonders why this keeps
happening. She sees her school clock tower in the distance, practically
mocking her at the time.

"Waaaaaaah! Dont be so mean!" she whines at the clock tower, as futile as
it seems, she sighs realising it as she starts running.

She starts her run with a slow pace as her long legs stride giving her an
impressive amount of speed. She looks down at them seeing the rythm she's
giving. Lifting her head looking straight she pushes herself to run faster
as the wind flies through her hair, sending her skirt flapping. She smiles
realising that she's making adequite time, realising she might just make it
to school on time. With determination she adds more speed to her running
watching the graviton high clock tower giving it's threats of tardyness
with it displaying 7:57.

"Oh no you dont! Im gonna make it!" she says defiantly running faster.

A trailing dust cloud forms behind her while she's running, her eyes locked
onto her destination, she fails to notice shattering buildings and a larger
dust cloud on an intercept course comming from downhill.

Kyanii sees the gates of the school as the clocktower displays 7:58, she
grins as she feels victory in her grasp.

"Im gonna make it!!" She cheers her self raising her arms in victory as if
winning a race, the race for time. But she quickly finds herself picked up
in a gust of turbulence as A-ko zooms past her carrying lil C-ko to school

Crashed on the ground in an awkward position Kyanii whimpers seeing the
clocktower move it's arms to 8:00 as if proclaiming it's own victory.

"This is not happening." she whines picking herself up slowly. "What else
could go wrong?"

She bends over to brush off her bruised knee she gets slapped in the fanny
by the school pervert as he passes her.
"Your late catgirl, get your cute tail to class before your a detention
jocky."

Kyanii grumbles and picks up her bookbag and backpack running into school.


[Part two comes soon, where I get my first taste of battle] -Kyanii Toragami
~
