Subject Magic 101?  Caemal starts his training.~
Text
(`2O`@O`2C `1n`!o`1te`#:`` After much pondering, I think you should pronounce the name K-mal)

``    Caemal sat down on the ground in the grasslands a short distance
north of Neo Tokyo.  For those who might not know, which I imagine 
would be many of you, Caemal is a young half Human, half Elven man,
aged at about 16.  He wears casual clothing and stands about 5'10".
His light blue hair was blown about by the wind as he opened a book.
It was labeled '`8Beginner's Tome of Black and White Magic Spells``'.

``   "`^How hard can it be, right?``" Caemal asked himself as he started to 
read.  "`^Let's see...she said to start with 'Pure Light'.``"

``    He scanned the page with his brown eyes, attempting to memorize the
spell while also reading how to cast it.  "`^Feel the energy?  What the``
`^heck does that mean?  Can't it be more clear?``"

``    "`^Whatever,``" he said, "`^I'll give it a shot.``"  He held one hand out, 
palm up, and said, "`^Forces, your light bestow, let the path be shown!``" 
Nothing happened.

``    "`^Huhn...well that was a bust.  Damnit, aren't these supposed to be``
`^the easy spells?!  Maybe I just suck at this?  Oh well, I'll give it ``
`^another shot.``"

``    He concentrated more this time...it looked alot like he must have 
been giving himself a headache.  "`^Forces, your light bestow.  Let the``
`^path be shown!``"  A blinding flash was emitted, which looked just like
cloud-to-cloud lightning from the city.  ...but there weren't any 
clouds.

``    "`^Aaagh!  Too bright!  And it burned itself out like that.  Maybe I ``
`^need to back it off a little...``"  He shook the temporary blindness out
of his eyes and read from the book again.  "`^Focus while relaxing...``
`^man, this is hard.  And it doesn't make any sense.  How can you relax``
`^and focus at the same time?  Sheesh...must have something to do with ``
`^'clearing your mind' and that stuff.``"  He took a drink from a bottle of
water, then stood up.

``    Caemal put the book down and stood straight.  He held his right hand
out palm-up and chanted the spell again, "`^Forces, your light bestow. ``
`^Let the path be shown...Pure Light!``"  A ball of light appeared in 
Caemal's hand, with brightness rivaling that of a candle's light.  He
let his palm down and the ball floated there for a few minutes, then 
faded away.  "`^Hey, I finally got it to work!  Cool!``"  He posed with an
anime-style victory sign.  "`^Kinda weak, but it's a start I guess... ``
`^let's try it again.``"

`8F`&i`8n``

--`@R`#P``-`6D`^a`6n``
