Subject Tavis's Anime Persona -- Batanen's Writing Contest~
Text
Tavis the Wandering Knight of Malta
Tavis is a name from a Dungeons and Dragons book I read along time ago.
Tavis Burdan is the full name.  He was a Knight who protected the weak even though he had fallen from grace.
I carry on as a Knight because my family bloodline started in the 1100's with the Knight's of Malta in real life.  This character attracted my attention because of the honor he prides himself with though his family name was disgraced.
My family name was never disgraced but it reminds me to mind and respect elders and others.

The first Anime figure I would use to help describe my personality would have to be Jubei from Ninja Scroll.
He has the heart of a warrior and the desire to succeed yet even the small price is enough.  He is not after money, just respect and honor among people and small villages.
In Ninja Scroll Resurrection (Part II) Jubei is disgraced for killing the wrong person after believing a lie.
This strengthens my characters name from the book as he was disgraced as well.

My second character would be Terry Bogard from Fatal Fury.
He constantly gives and gives to help protect the weak and innocent.
He strives to be a strong fighter and gain the respect of his peers, but also fights for the pride of the strangers around him.
He has the power to move the mind.
As I try to do when I gain friends.

My third character would be P. Jack from Tekken
A robot with the heart of a man.
I sometimes walk around pointlessly but if some one asks for help I strive to do all I can to help them.  
Hes a huge robot standing about 7ft tall and all muscle, much like I wish I could be.

My fourth character would be Cell from Dragon Ball Z.
Hes quite evil, however he has a sense of humor and he likes to play with people's minds and spirits.
Although my character is not evil, he does have the ability to manipulate minds and gain the respect of others through show of power and ability.
He is also very respectful of others much like Cell, until disrespected.
As a Saiyan my character is also like Cell in that he gains power very quickily.

My fifth and final character would be Vegeta.
I am sure everyone knows hes a evil guy turned good.
But hes also my favorite character because his boosts his ego and shows off his power with pride even when hes not the strongest.
He carries himself with pride because he knows how much work he puts into his strength.
Vegeta is the main part of my character because he also resembles a part of myself.
I like most people and respect most people until they disrespect me.
rpnote +

Overall I am a saiyan warrior who prides himself is gaining power and friends.
I am always looking for a way to become stronger.
~
