Sender  Trepid~
Date    Tue Apr 30 23:42:25 2002~
Stamp   1020228145
To      all~
Subject Anime Characters I Identify with.~
Text
There is a common theme among the characters I identify with... Several, really. My personality varies with the situations I face, so a general description would take far too long.
My three choices are: Cho Hakkai, from Gensomaden Saiyuuki; Urashima Keitarou from Love Hina; and Jou Kido from Digimon. The reasoning is as follows:
Cho Hakkai: I connect with the quiet, usually level-headed youkai from G.S. because of his great patience and tolerance for the actions of those around him, his surprising tendency to forgive all but the most heinous acts, and his honor.
These are traits I admire, respect, and have always strived to emulate, because frankly, the world doesn't need another hot-headed vengeful scoundrel. The path of compassion that Cho Hakkai walks is my own; we both help those in need.
...
Except when our family or friends are threatened. Cho and I shrug off humiliation in stride, use our senses and minds to avoid trouble, and allow our friends to be themselves.

Urashima Keitarou: While it would be fun to live the life of the Hinatasou Dorm Resident manager, I identify with him more for his work ethic and devotion to promises than I do with his strange ability to attract women. 
Of course, I wish I could share that ability... But that ain't happenin'. Urashima is an honest and reliable guy, for whom good intentions often backfire and end up requiring long, drawn-out explanations to correct misunderstandings. 
Welcome to Trepid's real life. Whenever I do something nice, it inevitably ends up with someone walking off in a huff. 
Like Keitarou, I am a pushover for many people, enabling easy manipulation through guilt to put me into unpleasant but necessary jobs and tasks. In my eagerness to help others, I will often put myself in embarassing or difficult situations.

Jou Kido: The original anime character that made me think, "Hey, that's me!" Reliable, intelligent, worry-wart, a nit-picker, the son of a doctor...
Our similarities are in personality, background, upbringing, and to a certain extent, physical appearance. Jou and I are fanatical about school work, constantly worried about our grades, and seek approval from our parents and friends.
Like Jou, I have basic medical training from my parents. I'm also deeply cynical and sarcastic, which is a trait he has, but to a much lesser extent. I look at the practical side of things, over-prepare and end up appearing slow of thought.
also have a clumsy side, and suffer what can only be called 'Spaz Attacks'. I am a fountain of random knowledge (Remember the anti-bakemon chant?) and analyze the situation. 
My only real difference from Jou is that I don't panic during a crisis, and I joke a lot more.

That's enough, I should think.  If you know these characters, you'll see one more connection. We all wear glasses of some sort (I'm counting Cho's monocle as glass, as it's only half of a glasses... so what if the eye behind it is damaged?)
Yours Etcetera,
Trepid.
~
