Sender  Yoiko~
Date    Sat May  4 11:58:54 2002~
Stamp   1020531534
To      all~
Subject Writing contest~
Text
The anime character that reminds me most of myself is a rather
hard choice for me to decide. Mainy because I feel as if there
were many characters that reminds me of myself. I'm sure quite
a few people probably feel the same, but since it was narrowed
down to a small selection to choose.. I think I'll pick the ones
below:


`&1: Rei Ayanami``
Rei is a mysterious person in my opinion. Sometimes she can seem
to be emotionless and cold to everyone around her, but.. to the
right person, she shows her heart to them. Rei cares alot more
than she lets on, even going as far as to sacrifice herself in
order to protect the ones she cares for. She is one of the anime
characters I feel closest with because while everyone normally
views me as one thing.. inside I am completely different. And
just like Rei, it just took that one special someone to draw out
who I really am. At least.. that's how I feel about it.

`&2: Sylia Stingray``
The Sylia I speak of is from Bubblegum crisis 2040. She is very
intelligent and professional, yet at other times she can be
very emotional. I love how she is portrayed, giving her the feel
that I can relate to her. I know that I can and do come off as
very cold and uncaring at times like Sylia, but it doesn't mean
that I'm cruel and cold hearted. Sometimes it takes a strong will
to get things done, even if it means sacrificing my own or sometimes
other people's happiness. It's not something I am proud of.. but
everyone has their bad qualities along with their good.

`&3: Ken Shiro``
Now this man is my hero. He's extremly violent and powerful, blowing
away his enemies with no mercy. On the other hand, this man is also
gentle and kind, using his skills to help and protect those that
need it. Even though he does all this.. he has something he holds
in his heart and mind. An obsession. Ken is very focused on
finding the woman he loves and destroying the one that took her away.
Many can claim to have a violent, bloody nature about them and I
am no exception in this case. But that is not what he mirrors about
me. It's his determination.. that impossible will to overcome all
obstacles to achieve what he seeks. I myself am very similar.. when
it's something I seek, I will overcome everything to achieve it, no
matter what. Then again.. I could say his obsession could match me
since I'm still here, playing on animemud after what? 5-6 years maybe?
Hmm.. guess I do have an obsessive nature also.. O_o;

`&4: Impmon``
What? Don't stare at me like that! So I like the show, so sue me.
Anyway.. Impmon is an interesting character. He spent his time trying
to achieve true power, but when he finally recieved it.. it controlled
him instead of the other way around. Because of his lust for strength,
he hurt many people and friends in order to get what he wanted. I can
relate to him easily due to his plight. I myself once was like him,
seeking power where ever I could obtain it. Yet.. when I finally had it,
the point of it seemed stale and empty. Just like Impmon, I had to deal
with my past deeds that followed me around like a dark shroud. Just like
him, I learned from my mistakes and emerged a stronger person in the
end and I have those that love me to thank for it.

`&5: The Overfiend``
Erm.. well this is self explanatory. Everyone knows I'm a big pervert
but I'm not all that bad! Really! I'm just.. misunderstood in my overly
affectionate nature. You believe me, right?

`&6: Haruhara Haruko``
The ever enigmatic being known as Haruko. I relate to her possibly
the most of all. Not much is really known about her and what was learned
may not nessicarily be true. The same applies to me as I often hide my
true self from others. Maybe it's for a secretive reason or maybe its
for my own gain. Despite this dark fact.. I am still a very playful
and affectionate person. Just like her, I really love causing mischief
and other forms of unusual trouble, but normally I mean no harm.
~
Sender  Fatetaf~
Date    Sat May  4 12:42:54 2002~
Stamp   1020534174
To      all~
Subject RP contest thingie~
Text
Megaman X 
I can relate to the problem X has. He wonders if ever one day 
he'll become a maverick.
I understand this problem because I myself, wonder if I'll ever go
to far in doing something evil.
Like, today I could be just chillin out.
But perhaps tomorrow I might go too far with something and it'll backfire.

I'm kinda like Vegeta (just like everybody and thier grandma)
Ok, So everybody relates to this guy.
It's human nature to hate and to have a superiority complex.
I can relate to this character in three ways.
The first is I obsess with things that I fail at.
If somebody beats me say at a game, I'd obsess with it until I can beat them.
This can be applied to a lot of things I do in real life even mud, if you want to get technical.

Another way I can relate to Vegeta is some days, I just hate everybody and everything.
I can wake up on the wrong side of the bed and I want to totally destroy the world.
Then there are times when I feel that nothing good ever happens and that it's all not worth it.
An unwanted feeling, that if I could just snap my fingers and blow up the world, I just might.
But then there are things that are in fact worth fighting for. And sometimes we loose sight of them,
because of our want for self and to be the best and have everything better.
But sometimes we stumble onto things that are worth sacraficing a part of ourself for.
Instead of fighting for ourselves, we fight for other people and at great expense to ourselves.
A contradiction of who we believe we are.

The third way, is I think too much to ever truely admit I am 100% wrong.

Vash the Stampede
I believe I am like this character mainly because I have REALLY INCREDIBLY bad luck.
Whenever something can go wrong, it does.
Like walking down the street and tripping on the curb.
Or perhaps items falling out of cabinets onto my head.
And when trouble can follow me, it does.
Luck with women included.
And no matter what I do it just kinda eats at me.
Like you never really get some rest. And say you take a vacation or something, it's never enough.
But I guess that's how we live.
It's kind of like, you don't enjoy the good things like peace and quiet, until you know what
it's like to suffer and actually know true hurt.


Kazuya Mishima
I can partially relate to this character.
Kazuya had a father that was never there for him
but when he was, he was throwing him off cliffs.
When I was younger it wasn't uncommon for me to be pushed down a stairway, 
fingers slammed in a door, punched, or kicked while down.
I can strongly relate to that aspect of it.
I have a strong hate towards my father but also at the same time,
I feel he is my father and I can't hate him. Otherwise I might not be any better.
It's hard to explain. So I won't :p


Ashram
rp + I can relate to Ashram in one way.
Ashram would finish what he started, even if he knew he was wrong.
I can relate to that. I would do something that I figure out midpoint that it's wrong. 
Knowing it's wrong I would still do it because I already decided I would.
It's mixed up honor, in a way.
Like if I give my word to somebody that I would help them then later on figure they have
bad intentions, I would still help them because I gave my word.

I know i'm not the greatest person in the world...
But I try to excuse that by not being the worst.

I was never any good at writing essays in the first place.
-Don
~
