Subject Batanen's Quest.~
Text
The characters I would define as being simular to Sirus Mekari:

`&Parn - Lodoss Wars: Chronicles of the Heroic Knight``

In the third offering of anime set in the world of Lodoss, you see Parn as a proud,
expierenced Knight who uses his abilities to help further beneficial progress to
the world. This character's honor and attitude towards the world helped me to flush
out exactly what I wanted to do with this character's causes.

`&Arshes Nei - Bastard``

The Thunder Empress Arshes Nei is a woman who was socially stratofied and put into
a catagory of people who do not fit in to their homelands. Caught between two worlds
and choosing to loose her emotional pain by loosing herself in her causes, she has
a tough but noble life. Also, the way she is cursed to eternally be stricken by her
love for those close to her is something fascinating and relatable.

`&Himura Kenshin - Samurai X``

Keep in mind, I do not mean the Kenshin from the television series, but the one from
the Samurai X OAV prequel series. Hardened, disiplined and uncertain. His life is one
heart wrenching pain to another, and all he has is his amazing skills to keep him
from uncovering the pain in his heart. Under the layers of cold blooded killer lies
a personal, albiet almost niave, dream of making the world a better place. His mind
and sword are in consitant combat with his heart and dreams.
~
