Text
The news channels are alive with the stories of the recent vampire attack increases in Neo-Tokyo, and
they're showing the story on almost every channel. One in particular covers the events as they unfold
trying to make the public aware, so that these foul creatures might possibly be stopped.

`6Female News Anchor: '`^Hello, and welcome back. This is Tara Mikali reporting once again as a new wave
of savage vampire attacks sweep across the city. In the past week, vampire attacks have increased dramatically
across the city, prompting people to form mobs and gangs to attempt to hunt down these creatures where
they dwell. The leader of Vampire Hunters has been urged by the public and City Hall to do something about
this upsurgence in attacks to no avail. Some people even claim that the reform of Vampire Hunter has
angered the vampires, causing them to attack more frequently and more savagely. Other still claim that
Vampire Hunter themselves are behind these attacks, in order to gain public support once the threat has
been sucessfully dealt with. The leader of Vampire Hunter was unable to be reached for comment.

`7Tara looks off to the side of the screen and nods, then looks back with an upset look on her face.

`^'A new report just in. A trail of bodies, drained of blood has been found in the streets. The count stands
at somewhere around 7 so far. Reports from citizens are telling of attacks on innocents sleeping in 
the streets. Citizens are urged to sleep indoors, and not to venture out during the night, when these 
creatures hunt most frequently. Safe houses are being set up throughout the city where people can sleep 
safely, without fear of being attacked. I urge you, please use these safe houses, and hopefully Vampire
Hunter will do something to rid us of the evil that plagues our streets.

`^This is Tara Mikali, signing off and urging all of you to be safe, and careful out there.

`7She pulls out her earpiece and lays it on the desk before turning slowly and standing up. She covers
her face with her hands and walks off stage as the news broadcast fades to commercial.


`7S`8e`7r`8i`7th `#- `!H`1unting `8the `&H`8unters``

