Subject The hunt is on.~
Text
The dark stranger watches this latest news report and frowns to himself as Tara's face fades out. "`1It's getting worse...I need to hurry and purge the rest before it's too late.``"
As he says this he draws his rapier from the heart of the vampire he'd pinned to the wall while stopping to watch the report, and in one swift motion removes the vampire's head from it's shoulders.
He turns to go, cloak whirling dramatically behind him. (`6The sun will be up soon, it'll be harder to track them.``) He pulls his hat low over his eyes and walks away, sheathing his sword and preparing to hunt his next "victim".
He thinks as he walks that there must be a better way to find them, a simpler way of locating them. (`6I wonder if perhaps this woman, this Tara Mikali might know of someone who could assist me? I believe I shall go and ask her.``)
He walks into the shadows, and seems to fade away.
