To      all~
Subject A meeting of sorts...~
Text
I prowl the streets again, once more stalking the night looking for unsuspecting
prey. Tonight however, the scent of something else is in the air. Another predator.
Something much... older than myself. I'm drawn to investigate. It's been so long
since I made contact with another of my kind.

I sense him, his presence, just around the corner. The night seems to freeze,
silent and still as I approach. I peer from the rooftops, spying him in the
perfect darkness.

I whisper to the stranger. '`^Hey, you there. Come over here.`7'

Myshiel replies without turning. '`^Why?`7'

'`^I wish to speak with you.`7' I reply cautiously.

Myshiel looks over his shoulder at me, saying '`^Can't, you are the enemy.`7'

I look down to Myshiel and sigh, relaxing slightly. '`^Damnit... how am I the enemy
already?`7'

Myshiel replies '`^I don't hang out with blood thirsty killers.`7'

'`^Oh.. that.`7' I say, motioning to a freshly drained corpse lying in a dark alley.

Myshiel turns, looking up at me. '`^I don't hang out with vamps.`7'

Myshiel replies '`^I feel uncomfortable alone.`7'

'`^You don't even know me yet...`7' I say, feeling a bit taken aback.

'`^Besides..`7' I say '`^you ARE a vamp... remember? You're one of us, whether
you like it or not.`7'

Myshiel snickers a bit. '`^Please, young whelp, I was a vampire before you were 
born as a Human.`7' 

I shrug. '`^Ok... you got me there.. I am young. I smell the stench of the ages 
coming off of you like the dust from a long forgotten tomb.`7'

Myshiel replies, ignoring my observation. '`^Besides, I will be investigating the 
murders.I am sure I will run in to you.`7'

'`^Probably..`7' I say, feeling a bit infamous all of a sudden. '`^I'm on the news a lot 
lately.`7'

Myshiel nods. '`^So I see.`7'

'`^You know...It's not my fault I'm a murderous bloodthirsty monster...`7 '
Myshiel stops momentarily. '`^Yes it is, Liar.`7'

'`^No,`7' I insist, '`^I'm only really ALIVE right after a fresh kill..I need to feel that again...`7' 

Myshiel spits disgustedly. '`^You're not alive.`7'

Now, it's my turn to ignore as I continue. '`^So you see, killing is my life, my 
sustenance...I taste life when someone dies.`7'

He stares at me deeply, contemplating this for a moment before replying.'`^Do 
you think that is what your killer felt?`7'

Caught a bit off guard I reply. '`^My killer? As in the one who made me?`7'

'`^Yes, is that what your creater felt?`7' He asks, staring me down for an answer.

Flustered, I respond, '`^I don't know the mind of my maker. Only the taste of his
flesh and the feel of his blood settling in my stomach.`7'

He shakes his head slightly, as if remembering a past event. '`^It is too bad. 
Youth these days don't have the proper upbringing. Perhaps this 
explains your lack of respect for that which you do not have.`7'

I scoff slightly, '`^Perhaps your ways are outdated. I think this meeting is over. 
'`^Maybe we'll meet again in a different place and time.`7' 

I turn to head back into the darkness, and when I look back for the stranger, 
he is gone. Nothing remains except for the slight stench of
old death lingering in the air.


`8Se`7r`8ith `#- `!H`1unting `8the `&H`8unters``
~
