Subject A Cold Wind...~
Text
Neo-Tokyo is ridden with chaos and fear concerning the sudden vampire menace. Though
the clan calling themselves Vampire Hunter vows to bring a swift end to this plague,
thier failed efforts to so much as spot a single vampire has left them with no 
confidence from the Neo-Tokyo population. Hence, the mayor of Neo-Tokyo has had to 
resort to more devious means of ending this increase in vampric murders...

The Mayor slams his fist against his desk glaring furiously at the man across the room.

The Mayor booms '`^I am trying to produce a solution for the reason my public cannot``
`^walk the streets after sunset without fear of being mutilated by one of those beasts``
`^and you can only think of your benefit from this?! Who the HELL do you think you``
`^are, sir?!``'

The figure across the room smirks allowing only thier mouth to enter the light,
keeping thier face concealed by the shadows in the Mayor's office. What they do allow
to be seen is a mask of humanity. The skin being light blue and dead, no lips just
a slit in the figures face.

`7The Man calmly responds '`^I am your only solution to this mess, Mayor. It seems your``
`^'Vampire Hunters' have been doing quite the bang up job. I'll get what you want done``
`^immediately. No investigation or questions asked. All I require is a simple payment``
`^for my services.``'

The Mayor growls '`^Your 'services' are deplorable, sir. I will not allow a scandal to``
`^to ensue within the council, even if it helps the public take thier minds off of the``
`^vampires.``'

The Man tosses a polaroid onto the desk from the shadows, it portrays a young man's
corpse found in the Training Arena, mangled, puncture wounds perforating his throat
in numerous areas.

The Man emotionlessly explains the photograph '`^That body was found not more then a`` 
`^few hours ago. It had been there for at least a week, rotting. A young sword pupil``
`^who met a very ugly demise, fed on to the point where his skin was dehydrated pre-``
`^mortem. How will it look if the masses find out that your law enforcement and 'Vampire``
`^ Hunters' didn't discover this boy's corpse for a about a week?``'

The Mayor studies the picture of the corpse in shock, the epidermis resembled the
Sands of Sorrow itself. Rigimortis had set in, eyes wide open filled with the ghosts 
of fear and sadness. The mayor turned away to look into his desk pretending the 
lifeless eyes of the young man didn't perturb him. He removed a velvet case 
concealing a monetary token from the lower drawer.

The Mayor whispered, trying not to wretch '`^One million now, one million when you``
`^have completed the task. Get rid of all of them.``

The Mayor threw the token at the figure, who deftly caught it in the shadows.

The Man huffed, retaining the smirk '`^How easily you officials bend under such meager``
`^strain.``'

With those final words the figure melted into the shadows. The mayor glanced down at
polaroid once more, then quickly dropped to his knees before the trach can and  
vomited loudly.

`1R`!u`#j`!i`1n `8- `6'`^You don't know what it's like, to be dead inside...`6'``
