Subject The terror continues...~
Text
It's a few hours past midnight, and probably the most dangerous time of the night. Serith awakens 
once more and decides to spread his particular brand of terror across the countryside. For him, the
nights are no more dangerous than they ever were before. For him, the darkness is where he hunts, where
he calls home. He glances briefly around his crypt, the old dust still settled and undisturbed. No
one had been here, he was still undiscovered.

He headed into the night, once more in search of prey, relishing the feel of the cool, damp, Neo-Tokyo
air on his face. Greeted by the sounds of the night, he concentrated on his senses, heightening them
to an unimaginable degree. He can feel the air moving from the breath of his soon to be victim, he
can hear the sweet vitae as it is pumped through their veins. He begins to track, following the telltale
scent through the sewers into the Underdark. His prey is near.

He stops to listen, to gain full knowledge of where his prey is, and what direction they are moving to
better prepare his ambush. Somewhere in the distance a television monitor drones on about the increase
in vampire attacks and the precautions one should take to avoid becoming a victim. He laughs slightly.

The time is now. He moves forward, sliding from shadow to shadow until the time is right. He dashes
from the seclusion of the darkness and strikes, quickly and unmercifully. His prey falls quickly, and
he relishes the taste of the blood as he drains it from their corpse. It tastes different. Not unlike 
human blood, but a bit more coppery, a bit more rich.

'`^Saiyan.`7' `6 Serith says, wiping the blood from his lips.

`7He moves quickly, retreating back into the shadows so that he won't be spotted and overwhelmed, and 
he heads back to his crypt, lightheaded with the rush of the feed. 

He was almost there when the scent of another filled his nostrils and he, still charged with the
last kill decided to go for another. Stepping from the shadows he leapt to attack and quickly sank 
his fangs into the neck of his next victim. They struggle, and he is thrown off as his victim flees.

'`^Another vampire?`7' `6Serith asks, watching his victim flee into the night.`7

He slinks back to his crypt, the blood of his kind still burning on his tongue. As he takes his place
for the night, he can't help but wonder where this new one came from, and what will come from his
attack.

`8Serith `#- `!H`1unting `8the `&H`8unters``
~
