Subject The Killer Revealed... Even To Himself~
Text
The Mayor watches the television diligently awaiting positive results to his efforts
in relieving the citizens of Neo-Tokyo from the vampire menace. He reaches over to
change the channel on the set when a man stumbles into the office. The Mayor stands up
immediately to inspect this sudden intruder. He is covered in his own blood, gashed
from legs to fore head, clothes torn apart revealing only angry wounds from something
that seems powerful.

The Mayor bellows, frightened, '`^What is the meaning of this?!``'

The Man looks up, his cold face washed with red. The assassin The Mayor hired had
apparently failed.

The Man mutters '`^That thing... is impossably strong...``'

The Man falls flat on his face breathing shallowly. No puncture wounds seem visible
leaving The Mayor to wonder what had done this to his investment. As the official 
rushes around the desk, the news begins to blare a woman's voice and triumphant yells
from the Neo-Tokyo citizens.

Tara Mikali cheerfully reports '`^Today is a great day in the city of Neo-Tokyo! People``
`^are rejoicing in the streets as the vampire murder has been brought to justice. This``
`^juvenile beast came into the law enforcement station to give himself up for the recent``
`^murders in Neo-Tokyo. His statement was short, as he was rushed off to the Shinto-``
`^Buddhist Temple, commonly known as Recall, for judgement.``

The Mayor watches in confusion as a familiar face appears on the screen, the young
vampire's face wrapped with guilt and streaked with tears.

Rujin Skyrender says '`^I'm sorry for what I have done. There can be no forgiveness``
`^nor recompensation for the lives I have taken in hunger. I will face the``
`^consequences as I must. I will never escape being a vampire, unless I am dead...``
`^and I fear my death is not far from now.``'

Tara Mikali nods as her face reappears on the screen.

Tara Mikali boasts '`^His Judgement will be held tomorrow, prioritized above all other``
`^court functions. More to come as the story progresses.``

The Mayor's jaw drops, the camera fades from news to commercials. The Mayor is 
absolutely speachless as not only all his efforts appear to be in vain, but the fact
that the murderer was so young... and seemed familiar.

`1R`!u`#j`!i`1n `8- `6'`^I shot the sheriff... but I did not shoot the deputy...`6'`` 
