Subject Until the Break of Dawn~
Text
The television cuts from the cheery evening programming to reveal the familiar intro of the Neo-Tokyo
Evening News. The intro plays, and the lights come up with the 'Breaking News' banner flashing across
the screen.
Tara Mikali stands just out of view in the back, partially shrouded by the darkened studio. She seems
to be struggling slightly with an unseen presence before she is thrust into the full light of the cameras.

Brushing back her disheveled hair, Tara looks into the camera, fear and concern easily discernable
on her face and demeanor. She straightens her shirt slightly before clearing her throat and beginning
to speak.
`^'Citizens of Neo-Tokyo, something terrible has happened. I've been told by... ' `7looking over her
shoulder into the darkness, `^' an.. informant, that the vampire called 'Rujin' who was recently
captured was NOT responsible for the mass killings in Neo-Tokyo. Rather, it is another, different vampire
that is menacing our city.'

`7She turns to look behind her, glancing over her shoulder into the darkness, and has only a moment
to flinch before she is overcome.

With a sickening crunch, blood spraying from Tara covers the camera, blocking it's view and briefly
obscuring the image of carnage happening in the studio. The blood runs down the camera's lens, revealing
a disturbing image of a man, or what seems to be one, feasting on the thick, warm blood gushing from
the enormous gash that was torn in her neck. He feeds, almost unaware of the camera still filming
until, finally sated, he looks up at the gore covered lens.

He walks closer, fully into the light revealing himself. `^'Greetings, Neo-Tokyo. I am Serith. It is, 
and has been me responsible for all of these killings. I feel no remorse, no sadness. You are my cattle.
Hide, flee, scurry into your homes. I'm coming for every single last one of you, and there is no place
to run. I am death, and I am hungry.'

`7He turns away, and with tremendous speed and strength, whips back to destroy the cameras, plunging the 
television into darkness.


`8Serith `#- `!H`1unting `8the `&H`8unters``
