Subject A Further Development~
Text
The mayor calmly breezed past his secretary and into his office, waiting for the door to close completely
before lauching into a screaming rage.

"`^GRAAAAAAAAAA!  Trust in Botouden?  TRUST IN BOTOUDEN?!  What a sickening thought.  As if the hunters
in this case are any better than the hunted!  Bigots and outright displays of patheticism, all of them!`7"

The figure standing on the other side of the office showed no sign of no sign of hearing the Mayor's tirade,
his eyes looking through the large glass back wall over the bright lights of Neo-Tokyo at Night.

"`^They rampage the streets...they kill their peers and enemies alike, destroy property and lives of
innocent citizens...all in the name of...not Good, not Evil, but themselves, no matter what they claim!`7"

"`6You would do best to calm yourself Mayor.  Your wife wants to know how you are, and you have a press
conference in twenty short minutes.  Keep yourself composed.`7"

The Mayor sighed, looking across his office at the gaunt figure.

"`^You're right...of course you're right.  You're going to take care of this for me, aren't you Bryson?
You know as well as I do that as long as they're all out there, no one will really be safe.`7"

Bryson turned, his hands in his trenchcoat pockets, leaning back against the glass.

"`6Oh I understand full well the intricacies of this situation.  Far greater than you do, and keep that
in mind.  The activities of Zero-T are neither your business, nor your concern.  But rest assured, things
will be rectified.  Now go.  You have things to do.`7"

Nodding rigidly, the Mayor brushed down his suit, straightened his tie, and left the office, leaving
Bryson alone.  After a few minutes, Bryson withdrew his right hand from his pocket, holding a small black
disc tightly.  He reached forward, and slipped it underneath one of the Mayor's desk drawers.  He then
withdrew his hand, and walked quietly from the office and down the street.

`4B`$r`&ys`$o`4n `7- So why are you running away?

(The following people should please read through this: all members of VH, Rujin, members of Unit-04, The SSIA, 
Rebels, any neutral parties, as well as anyone involved with the Zero-T RP strain (The former ATEs), and 
"Lafayette's Rally".  It will be beneficial in the upcoming quest/RP strain.-)

(Also, my apologies for the crappy formatting.  I had to write it so that it was easy to read by all parties, not
just RPers.)
~
Sender  Rujin~
Date    Fri Jun  7 12:11:11 2002~
Stamp   1023469871
To      all~
Subject What's wrong with me?!~
Text
Botouden and Meiko carry Rujin away from the holding cell. The young vampire is wrought
with guilt and sadness for the crimes he has commited sub-consciously. How could he
have killed so many people? was he the reason that news reporter had to die? The reason
for that psychopath Serith's actions? More then likely it was his fault, the things
he had done when he couldn't control that pain deep inside him, the pain of hunger.
He had seen so many things, travelled to other worlds, and finally he was home. 
Unfortunately returning to his home carried with it the curse of being a vampire. 
He was now forever one of the undead until someone put him out of his misery. Rujin
lost all care for life, life that didn't belong to this corpse of himself he inhabited.
His apathy began to anger him, his sadness began to anger him, the fact he was alive
trapped within this form was driving him insane. Nineteen years old again, his memories
of an eternity of battles, relationships, losses and victory geban to rise up inside
his mind. The fear of himself had turned into anger, the anger became hatred. Hatred
for the Methusela that made him what he was, hatred for everything. He no longer
lived, he hated. 

Botouden felt Rujin move, the young vampire was finally responsive and conscious again.

Botouden looks down at his fried yelling over the wind '`^You alright?``'

Rujin looked up at Botouden, the reformed hunters heart froze. Rujin's irises blazed
red, his eyes had gone black. Fangs jutted from the to and bottom halves of his jaw,
Botouden felt Rujin's mass grow as the muscles inside Rujin flexed and surged with
otherwordly power.

Rujin growls '`!Time for reckoning.``'

Botouden yelled in response '`^Rujin snap out of it! What the hell is wrong with you?!``'

Rujin twisted quickly, then pried open Botouden's powerful arms like they were blades
of grass. Rujin fell, straight down back into Neo-Tokyo towards the temple.

Meiko halted in mid-flight watching Rujin '`^What is he doing?!``'

Botouden rubbed his arms, he had tried to hold Rujin with all his strength and failed
miserably, Rujin escaped like Botouden was a small child. 

Botouden had halted as well next to Meiko, he looked over and grumbled '`^I don't know``
`^I had him one moment then he just escaped, he is stronger then I imagined.``'

Rujin flipped in mid-fall landing on his feet on top of the temple. The roof of the
temple cracked and boomed with the sudden impact leaving a crater on it's summit. The
young vampire gripped onto his hair shaking his head wildly. 

Rujin screamed '`!What's wrong with me?``'

Botouden and Meiko came straight down after him, Rujin looked up, his eyes filled with
hate, face twisted with rage and streaked with tears of pain.

Rujin roared '`!DIE!``'

Meiko looked over to Botouden on their way down and yelled over the wind '`^I think``
`^ we may have a problem.``

`1R`!u`#j`!i`1n `8- `6'`^It's coming, down on me, the hate is tearing at me`6'``
~
Sender  Ikazi~
Date    Fri Jun  7 15:44:47 2002~
Stamp   1023482687
To      all~
Subject Old wounds~
Text
Ikazi, the tall, dark man, watched the death of Tara Mikali for the umpteenth time as yet another station played it back. The story was all over every news station.
Pain contorted Ikazi's face. "`1I should have gone to see her before...``" As he watched the footage again, the painful memory he was trying to suppress slowly broke through.
"`1Lisa....It's happened again....``"
He winced as a new face superimposed itself over Tara's...Lisa. Millenia ago he had been unable to save her....And now this woman who resembled her so....
This animal...this....Serith...was going to die a slow, agonizing death...
(`6He will be easier to track at night....soon, though.``)
Ikazi was amazed at the amount of pain and anger welling up inside of him, awakening his long dormant lust to kill.
~
Sender  Aeron~
Date    Sat Jun  8 09:59:32 2002~
Stamp   1023548372
To      all~
Subject That night..~
Text
Aeron glances around herself sluggishly as she stares into the darkness from
inside the temple.  She blinks her eyes slowly and yawns, stretching her arms
and legs.  Her hands circle towards the front of her as she leans forward to
get up.  She had been sleeping.  Not something that is safe to do anymore, with
all the vampires running around.  She quickly checks her neck, feeling no bites, a small
sigh of relief escapes her lips.

`&---  `7Lots of screaming and yelling come from the market.  `&---``
Aeron's ears perk up, her eyes staring, narrowing, trying to focus in on something
anything, through the darkness that lays before her.  She gathers her things, backpack,
swords, and stands up fully.  Creeping towards the entranceway of the temple, Aeron
grips the hilt of her sword tightly, holding the blade at the side of her, cautiously.  It's
not likely to hear screams and the like, in this part of town.  She makes her way
out of the temple slowly, and then towards the fountain.  Hands beginning
to tremble, breathing becoming a bit heavier, Aeron nervously steps around the fountain
trying to get a better look of what the hell the commotion was.
She freezes in her steps as she sees two figures standing a good sixty feet
from her talking staring upwards.  She spins around and stares at the top
of the temple, a figure standing there.  Aeron's eyes grow wide as she
stands and stares, motionless.

The man on the roof screams out, '`!What's wrong with me?`7'``

From behind her, Aeron can hear the sound of two sets of footsteps running
her way.  She jumps backwards to get out of the way of the two men,
in their chase after this strange delusional man, who is now raging.
Then men on the ground pause in their tracks and converse for a brief moment then
take chase.

Aeron watches curiously, reaching for her second sword, grabbing the hilt tightly.
She brings the second sword around slowly, holding both of them relaxed and
limp at her side.  She stares in awe, not sure what to do, or if she should do anything.
The young man, on the roof, she recognizes.  Blinking several times, she squints
and stares some more.  The color from her face drains quickly, her eyes growing wide.

'`6That's.. that's.. Rujin....``', she says quietly to herself.
~
Sender  Serith~
Date    Sun Jun  9 14:42:40 2002~
Stamp   1023651760
To      all~
Subject A new development..~
Text
The commotion was unmistakable. It was everywhere, and the air was alive with anticipation, and the smell of something
Serith was very familiar with, fear. Slinking through the shadows, avoiding detection he crept towards the crowd gathered
around the temple. He looked towards the top, following the direction of the crowd and saw a man standing alone on the roof
bellowing in rage and anguish.

'`^Rujin... I thought he was still under lock and key...`7' `6Serith muttered quietly.

`7He crept closer, still trying to decide on a course of action to take regarding this new and interesting development, when
it hit him. Instinct, like always, won out.

Rujin roared atop the temple, screaming in rage and hatred at the thing he thought he'd become. His eyes glowed an angry
red as tears of blood streamed down his cheeks, staining them. The crowd below watched in fascination and horror as the two
figures high in the air paused, indecisive in their actions, and then at once turned back to the rooftop as another joined
Rujin on the temple. The crowd froze, and a silence washed over them as they realized that they were watching the very being
who had brutally murdered their beloved newscaster Tara Mikali approach Rujin, dragging a crying and thrashing child along
behind him.

Rujin stopped momentarily, focusing on this new creature who joined him on the rooftop, and then focused on what it was that
this creature had with him. A small child, crying and thrashing about, wishing only for it's mother, who screamed from the crowd
gathered below.

'`!What have you done here, fiend?!`7' Rujin roared angrily.

Serith stopped, a few yards from Rujin and pulled the child in front of him. '`^Nothing you wouldn't do too.. if you'd just
let yourself do what your instincts... what your hunger tells you to do.

`7Rujin stares in awe as Serith plunges his hand into the back of the child, spraying viscera and gore, and holds the now
limp child up in front of him. The blood from the young child runs down Serith's arm, dripping onto the rooftop.

'`^I know you can smell it... the blood. The life. Running from this young boy it can nourish and quench that hunger you feel.
It alone can stop the gnawing in your gut, the agony of starving for all time.`7' `6Serith said in a soothing tone.

`7Serith holds out the child's body, offering it to Rujin. '`^Drink. You have immense power, and an even greater hunger. 
Drink to sate the hunger. I can show you your power, and I can teach you to quench the hunger. Trust in me, and I will show
you the way.`7'

`6Serith waits a moment before saying `^'It's all up to you... '``


`8Serith `#- `!H`1unting `8the `&H`8unters``
~
Sender  Rujin~
Date    Sun Jun  9 15:03:12 2002~
Stamp   1023652992
To      all~
Subject Reflection~
Text
Rujin stared at the blood running onto the roof, when he had seen this monster kill
the child he at first felt rage, but watching the blood run onto the roof he felt
his heart sink into his stomach... all that blood being wasted.. and being so hungry.
Rujin looked up at Botouden and Meiko, Botouden's face was twisted wih rage. How
could that beast kill an innocent child?! Meiko had cupped a hand over her mouth
watching as Serith nonchalantly killed the child before it's mother. Rujin quietly
sat down on the roof curling into a ball.

Rujin mutters to himself '`!I'm so hungry...``'

Serith squatted down before Rujin, gently placing the child on the roof before the
young vampire. 

Serith calmly explains '`^What you are is not disgusting, there is no reason to hate``
`^yourself. You are superior to these sheep, if you do not believe me then prove``
`^it to yourself``'

Serith stood up awaiting Rujin's instinct to kick in, interested as to what would
result in his consciouss descision to feed on an innocent child. Rujin gripped onto
child's neck, standing up with the child in hand, staring at it like a ravenous dog
stares at a bloody steak hung before it. Rujin blinked, looking up at Serith.

Rujin growls '`!I may be undead, and a drinker of blood...``'

Rujin's instinct kicked in, but not to what Sertih was expecting. Serith had never 
known Rujin before, what happend next was unheard of in a vampire.

Rujin flung the child's body at Serith, catching Serith off guard and knocking him
down screaming '`!But I am not you!``'

Serith stood up growling, he drained the child's corpse of blood in seconds, then
flung the corpse aside like trash.
Serith roars '`^You fool! You would choose humanity over yourself?! Your not a``
`^vampire! Your a coward!``'

Serith rammed his fist into the young vampire's chest, throwing him off the roof
and all the way down into Market Square right infront of Aeron.

Serith cackled madly, Botouden screamed in rage then dove right at Serith against
Meiko's warning. Aeron unsheated both weapons.

Aeron screamed '`^You bastard! I'll have your head!``'

Serith watched the former Vampire Hunter and the Drow Elf rush him. He simply grinned,
blood trickling down the corners of his mouth.

Serith whispers in a near demonic tone '`^Look... more food for me...``'

`1R`!u`#j`!i`1n `8- `6'`^It's going down`6'``
~
Sender  Aeron~
Date    Sun Jun  9 17:34:06 2002~
Stamp   1023662046
To      all~
Subject BANZAI!~
Text
Aeron growls angrily, clutching both the hilts of her swords, like a hawk's talon
gripping prey.  The large hood of her black shroud drops to her shoulders, as
she runs full tilt towards the montrosity above her.  She leaps upwards gracefully with
great speed, holding her weapons in an attack-type style, landing on the rooftop
just inches from the edge.  Aeron stares at Serith, her golden eyes glowing bright amber,
gritting her teeth angrily.  She crouches down low, readying herself for any kind
of attack from the viscious vampire that stands before her.

'`3How.. how could you..?  In front of his mother!!``' she screams at Serith.

The vampire says nothing, but simply grins and then bursts into laughter.  His body
relaxed and unphased by the soon-to-be assault.
'`3Of course.. I forgot, your kind is superior.. You can do whatever the fuck you want!?``' she
says in a very sarcastic tone.

'`^Child.. Don't patronize me.  I don't have the patience.``', Serith hisses angrily, although
his face seems unemotional.

Aeron's motionlessness fades as she raises her two gleaming swords halfway
and charges at Serith, screaming.

'`3Die, you hellspawn!!!!``'  are the only things that escape from Aeron's lips as she lunges
at Serith.

The vampire raises an eyebrow and quickly sidesteps away from Aeron's futile
attack.  The drow slides to a halt and blinks for a moment, staring at the empty space
that was once filled by Serith.  She turns around quickly, swords raised in defense.

She blinks several times and stares at Serith, pondering.  '`3How.. the.. hell..??``'

Serith cackles insanely and says, '`^Weakling.``' and shakes his head slowly.

Aeron growls loudly, then relaxes from her stance momentarily, staring at Serith hazily.
She thinks to herself, '`2I've got to save Rujin.. he is not destined to be .. this.. way..``'

Seconds later she glances upward just in time to see Serith charging at her.


Aeron--  `&I'll be waving my hand..``
