Subject For anyone that enters the Kansas today..~
Text
Corpses have been arranged amongst the setup of the bar, seated as if they were
conversing and dining as if they were alive.  At tables, sidled up to the bar,
sitting against a back wall.  All of them have clawmarks and rips along their
throats and upper bodies, and their features are strangely hollow.  Their faces are
pale, eyes sunken.  Each and every single one of them is sitting with eyes open,
horrified look on their face, despite their arrangement.  Collectively, they look
horribly empty.

That's because their souls have been taken.  Each and every one of them.  Gone.
