Subject The Inn.~
Text
4:32am, Friday.

A boy glides by on a bicycle in the early morning air. As the pre-dawn begins to emit
it's haze from east, all the porches on 268th avenue are being pelted with the morning
edition of Neo-Tokyo times. The headline reads 'Strange murders baffle the Interpol
Tokyo Police'. The subheading reads 'What will be next?'. Under the subtext a few lines,
there is a picture of a saddened man with a look of hate in the edge of his eye. A text
under the pitograph reads 'A new hope rises in the midst of terrorist dangers'.

Elsewhere...

A man sitting at a desk sipping a Long Island Iced Tea smiles as he picks up an edition
of the AM paper. "`^So...``" he says, looking to a man in the corner with a suit on. After a
mock smile, he says, "`^Looks like this bastard did my job for me... no matter.``" He sips on
his drink and sets it down. "`^Soon, when fear sets into the heart of city, people will obey
what I say. They will fall into line out of fear...``"

The night begins to move into the day, and the man laughs from his secure office comfortably.

(OOC: Send in those notes. We need more people for this quest)
~
