The pink-haired girl smiled, watching her wavy reflection smile back.  She
slowly extended a finger out, poked the surface of the water and watched
herself dissolve and reform as the stream's surface flowed.  Bright
streaks flashed across the reflection as a school of minnows swam past.
Surrounded by waving prarie grasses, precariously perched on a large rock,
the pink-haired little girl in her blue dress would have easily passed for
something from a painting or picture.  The wide blue sky, the white puffy
clouds, the golden sun and the distant crow-calls gave the impression that
time had stopped, just so this one girl could enjoy the beauty of nature.

And in a way, it had.

[Keika/Suzuran Episode 4: "Here but for the grace of God..."]

The wind whistled, the grasses rushed, the insects scattered as nature
parted way for the blonde-haired girl on her broom.  Flying fast and low
over the grasses, the predator spotted her prey in the distance and
adjusted her course for a quick and certain kill.

Or shove, as the case may be.
Keika's hand caught Suzuran's dress square in the back.  Wrapping her
fingers around a conveniently-placed bow, Keika tore her sister free of
her perch on the rock and plunked her in the water before she could get
more than a surprised squeak out.  She didn't slow or look back, she
already knew her mission was accomplished. Keika turned sharply west,
again whistling over the grasses and leaving Suzuran to her fate.

For her credit, Suzuran was half-expecting something like this to happen,
and had deemed her actions as being Worth The Risk.  But a loss is a loss.
Suzuran dragged herself to her feet on the riverbank, attempted to wring
her dress out, sighed, and trudged off toward home, resigned to her fate.

Shortly home came into view, with Keika gloating on the porch.  She shot
an acid look at her soaked sister, turned her head toward a window, and
fired the final shot.

"Oneeeee-sama!  Suzuran is home, and she was at the creek again!"

Keika hopped down from the porch steps as the front door opened.  A tall,
elegant-looking girl stepped through, bearing a broom.  She blinked her
bright red eyes at the light, then smiled softly at the wet little girl
trudging her direction.  "Suzuran, what have you to say for youself?"

Suzuran mustered up all of her remaining dignity and threw it to the wind.
"KEIKA PUSHED ME IN!"

Keika snickered behind the tall girl's back, hiding behind her long blue
hair.

"Suzuran," began the tall girl, "you were told not to go to the creek,
correct?"

Suzuran sighed. "Yes, but..."

"Then you brought this on yourself by disobeying father's instructions."

Keika snickered again, drawing an acid glare from Suzuran.  The tall girl
stepped to the left, out of the doorframe. "Now go upstairs and change
clothes before you catch a cold. And I suggest you stay there until
father comes home, so that you don't cause yourself any more trouble than
you already have."

Suzuran silently trudged through the door, and the tall girl turned as if
to follow.  She stopped in the doorway and turned to see Keika picking a
book to read from a box on the porch.  "Keika?"

"Yes, oneesama?"

"What goes around, comes around."

Keika rolled her eyes.  "Hai, hai."  The tall girl continued through the
door, leaving Keika with her book.  Keika blew a strand of her long blonde
hair from her face, and turned to address a doll sitting on the opposite
end of the porch.  "Suiren is such a tool."

--- TBC ---
~
Sender  Serith~
Date    Fri Jun 14 13:43:29 2002~
Stamp   1024080209
To      all ~
Subject Let's Dance...~
Text
Let's dance..
Thinking to himself, Serith decides that perhaps the best course of action at the moment would be
to do nothing, only leave them thinking they are getting off lucky. Which, in fact, they are.

He charges Aeron with a tremendous ferocity, waiting for the instant her muscles contract in preparation
for his strike before stopping the charge. This sudden change in motion evokes the appropriate response
from a seasoned warrior like Aeron, and she does nothing, holding her guard, waiting for her opponent
to make the move. He lunges forward, anticipating the preemptive strike Aeron tries to deliver, and
taps into the powers inherent in his bloodline causing his actions to speed up to unimaginable proportions.

Not even a blur now, the world seems to slow to Serith so that even the quickest action seems to happen
in incredbily slow motion. The blood in his veins burns as the power he's using courses through him, 
and he knows he must make a quick decision before he can no longer sustain this burst. He moves quickly
casually stepping around the blades Aeron's hands hold out and moving around to behind her. Taking a
few strands of her hair in his hand, he nonchalantly sniffs them before letting them go and watching
as they hang in the air, falling impossibly slow back to her shoulders. 

He bends down slightly, opening his mouth to reveal his fangs as he lowers them to Aeron's neck. He
grazes her neck slightly with his fang, creating the smallest nick from which her blood will flow,  and
licks the wound quickly, tasting her flesh and blood in his mouth.
He whispers softly, '`^Next time, I won't take just a little..`7' before backing up and dropping off the
roof, disappearing into the night.

Aeron looks around astonished as her seeming attacker has vanished from right before her eyes, a whisper
echoing in her ears. She glances around unbelieving, her hand immediately going to her neck as she feels
a slight sting and the warmth of blood trickling down her shoulder.


`8Serith `#- `!H`1unting `8the `&H`8unters``
~
