Sender  Taskye~
Date    Fri Jun 14 17:36:05 2002~
Stamp   1024094165
To      all~
Subject The Infrequent Warble~
Text
This town isn't as I remembered it.
Much more personal, yet less violent.
You can imagine my astonishment.
I thought there was going to actually be a challenge.
But no, he's not here. I owe him.

The streets seemed to have been cleaned up some.
No injection needles lying around. Not that many dead cops.
But the scent is still the same.
The ancient paintings still have the scratches from combat.
It still smells like blood. The meaty chunky kind, like tomato sauce.

It's rather unreal, really.
Still, walking down the street.
A decapitated head is as common as a discarded cup or soda bottle.
A vampire spawning ground, really.
The air isn't as dark as it could be.
They must still be young.

There's no reason to let them grow older, however.
But not just yet. They scavenge for blood. 
I'll exterminate them.

I walked down the street, entering the Temple.
Still, the same sour candles burned. The same scent.
You would think it'd change after awhile.

When all the dreaming is over, you wake up.
Still got the crap in your eyes from the night before.
Still not sure if you're alive.
Certainly no new questions were answered.
I still despise everyone who isn't me.

The angels and the devils want to fight amongst themselves.
It matters not to me.
The innocent could one day become the guilty.
Might as well kill them both.
At least it'll be sure.
Only way to be sure.
At least I'll be sure.

~
