Text
(For those who don't understand what is going on, this is a continuation
of the Keika/Suzuran story I started originally.  I'll post the old
episodes as soon as I get copies of them.)
[----:----+----:----+----:----+----:----+----:----+----:----+----:----+----]

"This meeting will now come to order."

In a nameless meeting room aboard the Solar Miracle, the two surviving
Children, Ritsuko, Misato, and Fyuutsuki attempted to sort their facts out.
A ship with a new and nearly insane crew needed direction, and the directors
of the moment were busy getting their collective story straight.

"As the vice-commander of NERV, seeing as the Commander is gone,
I am now in command of this vessel.", said Fyuutsuki.

Everyone nodded.

"Umm, what's it's name?" he continued.

Collective facefault.

[Keika/Suzuran Episode 5: Donkeys live a long time]
Ritsuko nodded.  "This is the good ship Solar Miracle, the largest
created, ever. It was created at the same time as Headquarters,
under great secrecy, and then abandoned.  It's use apparently was as
an evacuation route if something were to happen during the construction
of Headquarters. It is unknown who originally constructed it, but it
was rediscovered by technical crews during the installation of the MAGI
system and converted from a submarine, it's original design, to a
spacecraft, and included in the Technical Department's evacuation
contingency plan.  It's purpose was to evacuate the core of the Department
and the MAGI, so they could be re-used in the event of an accident."

"So, you planned to throw the computers in here and save them, and just
forsake the rest of us and the EVA?", asked Misato.

"Yes," replied Ritsuko, "That was my mother's original intention."

A healthy pause ensued, which Asuka killed. "OK, so, now, what become
of the EVA, why are we here, when can we go home, and who's the new
girl?"

Misato paused, then answered. "As far as we can determine, EVA 02 is
destroyed and EVA 01 is in a low earth orbit - unrecoverable.  The
re-entry will destroy it.  We are right now orbiting Earth's Moon, and
the situation on Earth is worse than the one here - We can't even tell
what is going on, but all evidence indicates that Armageddon is taking
place, if not already over."  A pause.  "As for the girl...  The girl
is Suzuran Gyousei Majere, the pilot of this ship.  She was originally
given to NERV under unknown circumstances to be an EVA pilot - We put
her in EVA 00 and attempted to activate it.  On initial contact, she
held a 100% synchronisation ratio and maintained contact with EVA for
two days.  Then, suddenly and for unknown reasons, activation ceased
and could not be restarted.  Three attempts were made.  She simply told
us that EVA did not wish to talk to her anymore.  Since she was no longer
any use to NERV, but had a massive amount of technical knowledge, it was
ordered that she be killed.  Unfortunately, she managed to kill her
assasin, and instead she was designated to the technical department.
Shortly before my mother died, she sent Suzuran to the Miracle and had
her living there.  I was told of her existence when I was told of the
evacuation plans, in my mother's notes."

(CONTINUED IN NEXT NOTE)
~
Sender  Suzuran~
Date    Sun Jun 16 10:08:40 2002~
Stamp   1024240120
To      all~
Subject ...^2~
Text
"We only took her out of her hiding place once - To attempt to synchronise
her to EVA 01, shortly before Shinji's arrival.  She again attained a 100%
synch ratio on initial contact, but activation ceased 45 minutes into the
experiment.  The entry plug was force-ejected from the pilot's side.  She
told us the same story, that EVA did not want to talk to her anymore, and it
wanted Shinji Ikari.  This was strange to us, because she was not told of
Gendo's existence, let alone that of his son.  She said she knew nothing of
Shinji Ikari other than he was to pilot EVA 01.  And so, Shinji was sent for
and became the designated pilot of EVA 01.  Besides that, she has the
ability to be linked to the MAGI and synchronise with the MAGI processors,
much in the way EVA synchronisation works.  Mother's notes don't say,
but I suspect she was used in the original construction of the MAGI system."

Misato shifted positions from slouching in her chair to sitting upright.
"Wait, this makes no sense.  If she was around when your mother created
MAGI, wouldn't she be older than you?  She looks like a little kid..."

Ritsuko nodded again. "Her age is unknown.  She says she is 12, but she
has said this ever since I met her.  Based on her knowledge of world events
and factual information, I estimate her real age at around 700.  Either that,
or she spent an inordinate amount of time studying history from some very
detailed books.  And there's more besides that.  She has abilities that
Science cannot readily explain.  She has demonstrated ability to manipulate
objects at will, teleport herself at will, and other things."

"So wait," Asuka said, "You expect us to believe that she's a witch?
Older than dirt and knows magic?"

Ritsuko frowned slightly. "There is no such thing as magic.  I'm sure that
when I find out how and why she works, I can explain her.  Any sufficiently
advanced science looks like magic."

Asuka continued. "Well, why don't you ask her?  You should have lots of
information about her, since she was to be an EVA pilot.  Hell, they had
pictures of me IN THE NUDE in my files, even pictures of me as a baby!"

"Well," Ritsuko replied, sounding somewhat annoyed, "she WAS secret from
Gendo, I didn't have much opportunity to idly chat with her without risking
her detection..."

Asuka nodded, and muttered something under her breath in German.

Fyuutsuki nodded and stood. "So, now, what is our mission?  Where are we
going, and what are we doing?"

Ritsuko stopped glaring at Asuka and stared at the Earth, visible through the
room window.  "We cannot return to Earth...  The ship has no facilities for
landing and it looks as though Earth is undergoing global warfare anyway.  We
cannot go anywhere else because there is nowhere to go.  The ship is
self-sustaining; Food and water are generated inside the ship. I guess our
mission, for now, is merely to live.  For all intents and purposes, the crew
of this ship is the last of the human race."

The room grew noticably colder as this thought sank in.

===

Darkness screamed and swirled, chaos ripped through the world.  And Keika was
enjoying every minute of it.  She laughed above the hurricane winds as her glaive
ripped and tore at whatever was in range.  Unleashing her powers to their fullest
potential, she began tearing the world to pieces.  For a moment, she stopped
to survey her handiwork, as the world teetered on the brink of destruction.

(DAMN THE LINE BARRIER!  Next note, please!)
~
Sender  Suzuran~
Date    Sun Jun 16 10:09:37 2002~
Stamp   1024240177
To      all~
Subject The Return of ...~
Text
"Well, where are you now, Witch?  Where are you, to keep your promise?
Are you hiding around here somewhere?  Or have you given up?  Or do you really
even exist at all?  Do you really think you mattered to any of these people?
Do you really believe that these people cared at all for you?  Or do you
doubt?  In any case, I shall kill them all.  All you know, love, and care for,
all you have worked to create, I shall destroy, I shall kill.  And then I
will have that girl's soul of yours.  I will kill all that makes you, I shall
break you, and then I will kill your soul, and leave your wretched shell
behind to contemplate the error of your ways!"

The glaive rose, and the glaive fell, and the world was no more.

(To be continued)
~
