To      all~
Subject 22 june 2002~
Text
Dear Friend,

I hope you don't mind me writing like this, unannounced and all.  I was
told by a friend of mine who knows a friend of yours that I could talk
to you, that you would be understanding and not at all condescending
or unfeeling, and I desperately need someone to talk to right now.  My
mind has been running in circles ever since I got here, I feel lost and
confused; I hardly know where to begin...

Ever since I left home (I just couldn't take it anymore, the names, the
looks, the hate, because of what I am...you understand) I've felt, small.
Insignificant.  Inexperienced.  Like I'm all alone in a world that's too
big to care or even know about me, and it certainly won't start to any
time soon.  I'm losing hope...maybe I'm just genetically designed to
be a failure or something.  I don't know.

But I have met a few people, at least, here in Neo-Tokyo.  There's this
one man, they call him the questmaster.  He's friendly enough; he
lets me stay at his place, and gives me small jobs--rewards me
every now and then.  I think I'm beginning to get on his good side.
And all sorts of people come to meet him, they're all very 
friendly, and helpful, but they all definitely know this place
better than I.  It just makes me feel that much more naive.  I
guess that's the consequence of coming from a small village in the
country.  Oh well.

Anyway, I better go.  The questmaster needs me to pick up a harness for him,
I hope I don't have too much trouble finding it.  You don't know how much of 
help you've been, listening to the rant of a confused, unwanted, adolescent
dragonkin bum.  You're exactly what I've been needing.  I hope you let me
write you again.  Until then,

Your Friend,
Tuffer.
~
