To      all~
Subject Waking from a Nightmare, Into Hell pt.2~
Text
Kaoseraph approached Rujin, his appearance was about as comforting as a gun pointed
in your face by some lunatic. Rujin pressed against the wall, trying to pass through
it to get away from the thing. Kaoseraph chuckled at Rujin's fear, this was not how
he remembered the young vampire when he was alive last. Kaoseraph stood up straight
again and grinned.

`8Kaoseraph muttered `1'`!I wouldn't have believed it, if I had not had seen it``
`!with my own eyes.`1'``

Kaoseraph quickly took a step towards Rujin, who yelped and curled into a ball out of 
reaction. Kaoseraph boomed with laughter as he stepped back.

`8Kaoseraph laughs `1'`!So it's true! The warrior has become a child! I'll be damned``
`!again!`1'``

Rujin looked up, almost crying in fear of the thing `6'`^What... are you talking about?`6'``

Kaoseraph laughed, then swiftly leaned forward so he was face to face with the young
vampire, a viscious grin spread across his face.

`8Kaoseraph told Rujin, in a murderous tone `1'`!I am talking about one thousand``
`!years ago when you and me last fought. Then I was just a brash child, while you``
`!were a mighty warrior. Ironic, after the Apocalypse the tables have turned. I``
`!am now the powerful warrior, and you are just a child`1'``

Rujin moved slowly away from Kaoseraph, the things breath smelled like sulfur or
brimstone, it was making Rujin dizzy. Kaoseraph followed Rujin with his head the entire
way the young vampire moved.

Rujin cried `6'`^Leave me alone! I don't know who you are, or what you are!``
`^I don't even know really what I am! Please... just leave me alone!`6'``

`8Kaoseraph shook his head slowly `1'`!Sorry, can't do that.`1'``

Rujin lunged forward, swinging for Kaoseraph's head with his fist. The demon stood
straight up, caught the young vampires arm, and lifted Rujin off the ground. Rujin
struggled to get released. Kaoseraph smiled, cocked his head to the side, then with
a deft movement, broke Rujin's arm in three places. The young vampire screamed inhumanly.
Kaoseraph took Rujin by the shirt with his free hand releasing his arm, then slammed
the vampire into a nearby wall, making a crater in the stone and cracking a few of Rujin's
ribs like twigs.

Kaoseraph hauled the now unconscious Rujin over his shoulder, he open his hand to a
wall, and a gate exploded from thin air, opening into darkness unknown. Kaoseraph
smiled, and stepped through. The gate shut quickly, and then, there was silence.

`1R`!u`#j`!i`1n `8- `6'`^Leaving faith to die.`6'`` 
~
