Subject The search..~
Text
The young woman lands on the ground lightly, her swords drawn
upward.  She glances around quickly and concludes that area is safe.
She stands up slowly and sheathes her swords, drawing
her shroud around her.  The overhead lights are bright
and to an extent that surpasses her personal comfort.
Jades squints her eyes and continues to move down the corridor
that she had fallen into.  Her movements are fluid and quick
as she strafes throughout the hallway, looking down
connecting hallways.  She stops momentarily and hugs the wall
to her left, pressing her back flush to the metal.  Voices can be
heard not far off.  Jades dons the hood of her shroud and
creeps quietly towards the source of the disturbance,
listening carefully.

A man:  '`6I'm a dunpeal, Rujin unfortunately is becoming a vampire day by day.`7'``
A second man: '`6Botouden.. I've heard of you and--`7'``
Botouden: '`6Argyle.  I haven't found him yet.`7'``
Botouden: '`6I have some things to attend to.  Please take care of Rujin.``'
The second man: '`6Of course..``'

Jades doesn't stand to listen any further as the voices drift quietly
away, she's running swiftly down the corridor.
Anger wells up inside of her with every step in search of Rujin.

'`1This.. can't be.  Rujin turning?!  What is he doing here..?!``' she thinks to herself.

Jades pauses briefly scanning the area and sprints down an
adjacent hallway.  Her eyes flare of a dark crimson shade, her
movements hasten, surroundings blurring.  She stops again
at another hallway intersection, head swinging back and forth
quickly to scan the area, she jumps left and continues to run.

'`1I've.. seen this place before.  This is the VH compound...``'  she shudders
slightly at the thought but proceeds, more cautiously.

She gets ready to take off again but she hears a voice, a familiar
voice.  Jades stalks towards the voice, listening.  Sounds like
someone arguing.

A young man with a frantic voice:  '`6LEAVE ME ALONE! I DON'T KNOW WHO YOU ARE, OR WHAT YOU ARE!``'
Another man with a lower voice: '`6Sorry.. Can't do that.``'

Jades thinks to herself, '`1Rujin... !``' and stealthfully makes her way
towards the doorway.

She removes the hood of her shroud and grabs the hilt of one
of her swords in her left hand.  Jades twitches slightly, her
eyes glowing of a bright red.  She reaches for the doorknob
and grabs it tightly, then slowly turns it.
~
