Subject "A Leader of Men": Presidential Election Time in Neo-Tokyo.~
Text
`&4:28 am``

``     A lone figure leans upon one of the outside walls of an abandoned warehouse on the docks of Neo-Tokyo's
river, trying to escape the falling rain of a stormy night with shelter from the building's awning. A just-
as-lone street lamp shines down on the figure: a man dressed in a black casual suit, slowly puffing at the
cigarette held between the fingers on his right hand.

``     As the clock hits `&4:30``, a small ringing sound appears, emitting from the man's right pocket of his
jacket. He rests his smoke on his lips and pulls out a small black cell phone, flipping it's cover up.

`8     "`&This is Kun.`8"`` He speaks low, almost inaudible.

``     The returning voice is from an older sounding man. "`6Ah good, you're there. As you can see, I couldn't
it out there tonight, because of the weather. Sorry for the inconvenience. You understand, I'm sure.``"

``     Kun doesn't respond, rather he puffs at his cigarette once more, then throws it into the damp night.

``     "`6Down to business. The candidates for the presidential election in Neo-Tokyo,  are beginning to make
their rounds in the city, promoting themselves for the upcoming election. Now, you know as well as I that
there have been rumors of attacks being planned for the candidates.``"

``     Kun runs a hand through his brown hair. `8"`&And you want me to find out who's behind all this planning,
right Daiko?`8"`` His facial expression is serious, as always.

``     Daiko chuckles a bit on the other side of the phone, just to himself. "`6Well, yes. And keep the
candidates safe at any cost. I get the feeling I'm just repeating myself again.``"

``     Kun nods slowly. `8"`&What about the SSiA? Have they been confirmed to have a hand in this?`8"``

"`6At this moment, anything is possible. Be on your guard.``"

``     Kun nods again, switching topics. `8"`&As for `1C`!i`1rque`&?`8"``

``     Daiko pauses for a moment. "`6No clue. At this time, no one has heard from, or seen for that matter,
him at all. He may be AWOL.``" He sighs. "`6You and Kevin are all that is left of `10`!4`6.``"

`8     "`&Quaint.`8"`` Kun places another cigarette on his lips and flips open a chrome Zippo, lighting it and
a long drag. `8"`&Well then, I guess we're on our own now.`8"``

``     "`6It's what you're best at. Watch yourself.``" Daiko's side of the line clicks and he is gone.

``      Kun clicks off his signal and removes a small black part from the back of the phone, then promptly
tosses the cell into the river. Pocketing the part, he trudges off into the dark, wet night...

~
Sender  Tuffer~
Date    Tue Jun 25 09:10:00 2002~
Stamp   1025014200
To      all~
Subject 25 june 2002~
Text
Dear Friend,

I'm glad I'm able to write to you like this, you have no idea how much it
helps to have someone to open up to.  Especially since I'm so new here...
I mean, I'm learning my way around, it's just, difficult.  You
understand.

I'm still working for the questmaster, but...things have changed.  At first,
he asked me to pick up some lost items for him.  Simple enough, right?  Just
go around, explore a bit, help him out so I can have a place to stay, but...
well today he told me that there was a deadly criminal on the loose, and that
it was up to me to...to punish him.

I thought to myself, alright, I can go pick this guy up, take him to New Thalos,
get him put in a cell, and that'd be the end of it.  But the questmaster looked
at me and said, 'Son, you have to kill him.'

I was broken.  I'd never killed anybody before, I don't even know the first
thing about killing people.  But he said if I didn't I'd be on the street, and, I
mean, he was a criminal after all.  A murderer.  So I told him I would...I didn't
know what else to do.

So I looked up the guy.  He was an old man, a tax collector; he spent most
of his time jotting down numbers in a little notebook he carried with him.  I
watched him for a long time, strolling around, asking businessmen how much 
profit they've earned since last quarter, collecting his fees...he stopped in
the market, at an ice cream vendor.  There was a little boy there, smiling and
running around.  The old man beckoned him over, chatted with him for a few
minutes, bought him an ice cream...I couldn't help but wonder, when does the
evil in a person outweigh the good?  And who decides that anyway?

But I had my livelihood to consider.  And the guy was a convicted murderer.
So I followed him into a back alley...kept glancing over my shoulder, I was so
nervous.  So nervous.  I thought I would be sick, and then I'd fail, and be
homeless, hungry.  But I took a couple deep breaths and pulled out my dagger,
closed my eyes and stabbed him in the back.  I didn't dare open my eyes, I just
kept stabbing and stabbing.  His screams raked my ears like shards of glass, but
I couldn't let myself stop.  When he was finally silent and I felt his warm blood
on my hands I turned and threw up in the gutter.  I don't remember what happened
after that; I wandered aimlessly for at least half the day, numb.

I'm feeling a little better now, but I still shake on and off.  And when I close
my eyes, all I see is blood everywhere...like a swelling hot wave of death
breaking over me, and I'm torn away by the undertow.

Anyway.  I think I'm going to sleep.  I don't know what else to do.  Thanks for
being there, as always.

Your Friend,
Tuffer
~
