Subject the Sea of Souls~
Text
`7     Bright points of light cast dim shadows through the dust-ridden space,
lending some meager amount of dimension to the emptiness.  Sol burns with a
fierce intensity not far from the site of some disturbance.  Light bends and
distorts under its influence, the space itself warping in seemingly random
convulsions.  The expanse begins to buckle under the unseen forces, its form
screaming in silent protest as it begins to tear apart through the middle.
A storm erupts within its center, massive currents of energy flowing outward
in erratic bolts that seem to crawl along the raging black and crimson
clowds.  Tiny specs appear within the eye, growing larger slowly as they
approach normal space.  The objects appear to be interstellar ships, a great
fleet pouring out from the twisted canals of the Warp.

`7     Video broadcasts and radio transmissions flare into frantic use as
reports begin to filter in.  '`^..has appeared within the system, roughly four``
`^times the size of Earth, positioned within Saturn's natural orbit, and it``
`^has been estimated that in two months the anomoly and Saturn will collide``
`^with devestating results...``'  '`^...the unidentified fleet has begun a slow``
`^approach towards the Earth, their intentions still unknown at this time...``'
The reporter's voices are suddenly drowned out by loud static as the air
waves are bombarded by a flood of radio noise, filling the world with its
garbled message.  The seemingly random static blares out of radio's for over
two hours and then abruptly ends, blanketing all in silence.

`&Kurusa. `8-`7 Keep an eye out for future additions and
`7          possible quest announcments.
~
