Sender  Syke~
Date    Sat Jun 29 20:33:02 2002~
Stamp   1025400782
To      Sirus~
Subject Abandoned Weapons Facility ``(`&RP``-`6Q`^u`&e`^s`6t``)~
Text
Stumbling out of the forest, Syke wiped the sweat off from his brow.
Looking down at the small handmade map he had been given by Mr.
Klain, he was sure that this building was his destination. Good thing
too since he couldn't take any more of the rugged terrain he had traversed
to make it to his destination.

Stepping up to the large and slightly rundown building, he fiercely knocked
on the large metal door barring his entrance. The door opened a minute
later and a middle aged man in a labsuit greeted Syke.

`3'`#Ah, you must be errr... `3'``, the man began as he glanced at a small note he
he was carrying, `3'`#Syke! of course... yes, we've been expecting you. Come in!`3'``

Syke entered after the man carefully, inspecting his new surroundings while
listening to what the scientist of magic had to say.

`3'`#My name is Dr. Solem and this is my glorious facility! We've been working``
`#very diligently on quite a few projects. If you'll follow me this way I can``
`#show you some of our most recent work!`3'``. The Doctor lead Syke down a
narrow hallway and to a room where numerous other scientists were comparing 
formulas and talking quietly amongst themselves.

Syke followed the man towards the back of the room as the rest of the
interrupted their conversation to sneak a peek at their new visitor.
As the man began to open his mouth again, Syke decided to open his before
it would be too late to interrupt. `6'`^Doctor... I could really use some water``
`^right about now if you don't mind`6'``

The doctor looked quite ashamed that he hadn't thought of this and pulled over
what surely was one of his assistants mumbling something quietly into his ear
before continuing on with Syke.

`3'`#Well then! This wonderful piece of weaponry here is something that``
`#us at the lab have been working on for quite some time...`3'``. The doctor pulled
a small gun from a nearby drawer and brandished it. `3'`#Yes, well this here``
`#weapon has the power to shoot magically enhanced bullets and also is enchanted``
`#to make aiming much easier, setting the mind of the user at ease and calming``
`#his nerves..`3'``.

Syke, attempting to not be rude, feigned interest.
`6'`^That is quite a marvelous toy you have there, but I was wondering``
`^if you could offer me something a little more my style.`6'``. With that, he
drew his daggers, spun them once, and placed them back into
their holsters.

`#'`3Mmmm, of course.. Where is my mind today..`#'``the scientist muttered as he
as he walks towards the exit to the room, waving his hand in a beckoning
motion.

Syke follows quickly, much more interested now. Apparently there
was something quite specifically prepared for him.

Dr. Solem opens the door to the room with a special keypad code located to
side of the door, along with what appears to be a fingerprint scan.
The doctor walks quickly in and opens a small case in the center of the room.
`3'`#This is something you may find a bit more of interest...`3'`` as he picks up
a small dagger from the case and hands it to Syke.

Syke takes the weapon greedily and feels a surge of power that makes him
stagger backward, and simply stares at the dagger.

The doctor chuckles. `3'`#Never wielded a magically enhanced weapon I see?`3'`` and helps
Syke steady himself. `3'`#Easy there... this one has more power than most you'll find and``
`#for good reason... WE didn't make it, we found it`3'``.

`3'`#We've had it here for years... in fact, it's kind of what sprung Mr. Klain's``
`#interest in magical weaponry. However, as you probably can tell, our weapons``
`#could never compare in power to this fine specimen and he lost interest soon``
`#after. It was named Kotetsu after the village it was found in. I'm sure it``
`#will come in handy to you.`3'``

Syke pockets his new weapon in place of one of his Shadowslayers and
nods to the doctor in thanks as he leaves the building, having obtained
what he came for.
~
