Sender  Syke~
Date    Sat Jun 29 23:54:29 2002~
Stamp   1025412869
To      sirus~
Subject A new friend ``(`&RP``-`6Q`^u`&e`^s`6t``)~
Text
Syke emerged from the facility and quickly darted through the woods,
still wondering what the force was that had went through his body so
violently. He had worn many magically enhanced weapons in his lifetime
and none had given him such a powerful shock. To find out, he would have
to put his new weapon to the test.

Syke exitted the forest on it's far side, a bit tired from his
quick sprint, but none the worse off since his adrenaline was keeping
him quite alert. Now to test out his new weapon...

Being a thief had it's advantages. You got to know where the usual places were where
muggings took place, since you had to use them yourself, and any road between
two towns was usually a good place to start. Equidistant from both towns, the victim
would have a hard time calling for help and getting it.

Luckily, the directions were from a minor town so as to make them less confusing so all
he would have to do was follow the road out and look for some trouble. Not too hard
at all...

As he left the town, Syke took out his dagger, feeling another burst of power
surge through his body. This just made him more curious for answers as he
rushed down the path, in search of prey.

After travelling at a brisk pace for quite a ways, he finally found his victim
in the form of a band of thieves, making their approach from all directions.

`&'`8Listen up and listen well`&'`` cackled one of them. `&'`8We know well enough what``
`8occupation you're in, and that means you've probably got a good amount of gold on ya.``
`8Seeing as this is our territory, we think it's only fair that you ... share the``
`8wealth...`&'``

Syke nodded after the man was done talking and took out his shadowslayer so as
to have a secondary weapon. With a half-grin on his face he replied,
`6'`^Let's dance...`6'``

Syke jumped to action immediately, surprising his foes. In seconds, the thief who
had been talking to Syke had a deep gouge in his face and Syke was already behind him,
raising his Kotetsu and Shadowslayer above his head. Bringing them down with
great force, the thief cried out in agony. Now anybody would do so when getting a dagger
lodged in one's back, however even Syke could feel the immense heat radiating from
the Kotetsu on impact. The smell of burning flesh flooded Syke's nostrils, causing him to 
stumble backwards.

The dagger glowed brightly as it exitted from the young man's back, as though it
was aware it was in use. The sound of singing flesh and the speed with which
Syke had moved was enough to scare off the rest of the band.

Come to think of it, if he had seen somebody move that fast, he probably would
have run too... There was more to this dagger than he could possibly figure
out from one fight alone.

Sheathing his new weapon once again, Syke decided it was high time to head back to Erik's
office, so that he could relax and more clearly figure out exactly
what he was dealing with...

~
