To      all~
Subject Poem : The River of Life~
Text
`7T`8he `$R`^iv`$e`4r `$o`9f `1L`!i`7f`!e``
How I hate this wretched thing called life
And the pitiful people in it.
Im disgusted with the misunderstandings
And the tribulations that come with it.

What is the cause of this anger
Why doesnt anything suffice?
Is the world to be soaked in my doubt
For the rest of my entire life? 

People are the root of my hatred,
Acting as if they understand.
The lone question that drifts to mind
Is how they think they possibly can.

How well can you really know a person
With their thoughts and feelings as deep as the sea?
Is the human mind a locked chest of wonder
Impossible to open without a key?

This key, of course, does not exist,
For if it did, life would be grand.
The state of bonds between different people
Would then be coral-not broken sand.  

Is it unfair for me to hate them
Just for being so shallow?
Is it me whos the one at fault-
Is it me whos being callow? 

It hurts, as the realization settles in
That Im not as superior as I think.
Once Poseidon who ruled the sea;
Now a rock that merely sinks. 

Am I just a hypocrite,
Contradicting everything I say?
Am I just blaming others
So that I will seem okay?

As I examine the ideals flooding my mind,
Confusion pours down on me.
I spot the faults that fog my judgment of others,
For I am just like `&them``, as I now see.

How could I have thought that way-
Accusing those lacking empathy?
Why was I hating them for swimming too far;
Hating themwhen it was also me?

I hate the way that life works out;
Never right, almost always wrong.
Like waiting for that fish to bite;
Realizing it takes so long. 

Does realization change the principles 
Of my profound philosophy?
Or does it cause the stream of my beliefs
To simply flow to another degree?

I know whats in all of our minds:
Many thoughts drenched in assumptions
Even an idea so obvious as that
Would require to be labeled a presumption.

Without assumptions, what would happen
To this world within a day?
Would anything be accomplished
Without people presuming away?

This world must keep turning
Even if life is drowned in mist.
Assumptions are fine with me
If certainty cannot exist.

And so I cannot claim to hate life
Nor the people in it.
The only way to stay afloat in this river
Is to flow along with it.
~
