Subject don's rp poem quest~
Text
`8[`5the `6questmaster's `2demise`8]``

once there was a dragonkin who wanted to be wealthy.
he learned to thieve, and pinch, and steal, and gen'rally be stealthy.
the quickest way, he had to say--to reach his goal much faster--
was doing chores and other bores for a surly, stingy master.

this master was, on all accounts, a brimy sort of fellow;
his clothes were tattered horribly, his teeth were awf'lly yellow--
but even so, the youth did know that old man had some money,
so day by day he did his will,
he hardly had a moment still,
nor ever could he eat his fill
and his reward: the master's laughs.  that old man found it funny!

it went like this for months on months, the poor youth doing favors;
that dragonkin held up his chin, and even helped his neighbors.
but youthful strength and energy will never last forever,
and our poor lad sure wished he had some show for his endeavor.

and then there came a certain day, the master had a task:
'go fetch for me a remedy--' was all he got to ask,
for just as our old questmaster began to utter more,
the dragonkin ripped off his chin,
undid his eyes and pushed them in,
tore out his heart and ate it, then
engulfed the corpse in scortching flames and threw it on the floor.

so what, pray tell, in earth or hell, is th' moral of this story?
there's no quick way, i'm sad to say, to earning fame and glory.
but even so, for you must know, there's pleasure for earning,
and all it takes is killing those who keep you from your yearning!

4 july 2002
the end.  hope you liked.
~
