Subject Let the blades bathe again...~
Text
The bloodlust was upon him.  It'd been much too long since the demon had taken
part in the hunt.  He felt rusty.  Senses dulled, weapons dulled.  He was out
of practice.  He needed something to bring him back to fighting form.  A reason
to draw the blood of his foes again.

And that reason came, in the form of an invitation to rejoin INVID's Royal Guard.
Since he had left the Zalem outpost of the Hunter-Warriors, the demon had been
even more inactive than usual, and this brought about nothing but boredom.  After
rejoining INVID's ranks, the old bloodlust was rising again.  And no sooner did it
start, than someone decided it would be amusing to challenge the old demon.

One of the 'Saiyan Elite', a group of baboons who like to pretend they're more
than baboons, called him out.  This one was called Zebb, and apparently, he
thought he could prove a match for the old demon.

The battle was quicker than he expected.  As soon as it started, the saiyan was on
the run, fleeing from Lightsbane's blades.  The chase was swift, and Erik was
falling behind.  He almost thought Zebb would get away.  But a fatal mistake was
made when Zebb recruited the help of an old god, Zeus, into battle.
Zebb was still vulnerable to the demon's hellfire, and that was what brought
the saiyan down, setting up for one more fatal blow.

The blood was flowing again.  The old demon was happy again.
~
Sender  Erik~
Date    Fri Jul  5 18:50:20 2002~
Stamp   1025913020
To      all~
Subject Bloodlust...~
Text
The bloodlust was back in full swing.

The demon's old urges were coming back to him again.  The thrill of the
chase, the taste of the blood as he licked it from his blade.  The saiyan
had righted his path, but he wasn't sated.  He needed more.  Duels weren't
going to sate the urges.

He needed to hunt again.

News of one of the Judges' movement reached the demon in his rest, and
the hunt was on.  The Judge was preoccupied, attempting to kill someone who
had no reason to be judged.  The blades caught him by surprise, and the elf ran
like wildfire.  He was chased from corner to corner of the map, finally
being cornered amongst the cages of the Keeper in the Underdark proper.
The fight was ended there, the elven High Judge's blood spilled all over the
stone floor.

After taking a moment to spit on the corpse, the demon left, sated again.
~
