There once was a fool named Xenabu.
Who wouldn't pay off debts to the mob-u.
They collected their fees...
after breaking his knees...
And cut off his fingertips for their stew.

Xenabu swore, those bastards would pay!
Oh, a grand scheme he planned for the day
that he'd get his revenge
and finally avenge
the fingertips that the mob did filet.

He had explosives stacked up for miles!
The tower could be seen from the British Isles!
He piled them into his boat
and went to a remote
location.  The mob's base, it was Lyle's.

Lyle's was a diner on the bay.
The mob ate there day after day.
They ordered fondue,
and drank plenty of brew,
It was there they planned their foul play.

Xenabu brought his boat up to the dock.
And laughed as he detonated his stock.
Alas, he didn't get away.
But his body parts covered the buffet.
As the mob all laughed!  Oh, how did they mock!

Kids, let this be a lesson to you.
If the mob, you plan to undo.
When you mess with the mob,
Don't plot like a slob.
Don't get your bombs from their crew.
~
