To      vampire~
Subject Late at night...~
Text
``  Koren sat on the rooftop of the factory late at night, looking down 
on the world below her.  So often she had found trust and self-loyalty
in the position she often took, standing high above others.  It used to
make her superior to humans.  It used to make her better, higher, 
stronger...  Now, that loyalty and trust was gone...where was she to 
turn?
``  Superiority was no longer hers...was it?  She had failed.  Failed to
maintain a team, failed to even form one...failed her leadership, 
perhaps everything she had come to believe in since...
``  She looked out at the stars.  She had returned from years of 
imprisonment...years of torture and torment at the hands of things not 
of this world...nor this dimension.  Who had come to save her?  Who  
rescued her, after all those she once helped and saved?  No one.
``  "`^Hmph,``" she said, throwing a rock out.  It tumbled down the 
mountainside, coming to a stop who-knows-where.  "`^Silly thoughts.  Such
emotions need to be extinguished.  They can only get in my way.``"
``  "`^I'm safer off alone anyway.  Better off...  I don't have to worry 
about saving anyone, and no one has to be burdened with saving me.  
But...  Forget it, Koren.  That part of your life is over.  Thinking or 
caring about it now will get you nowhere, so leave the past behind.``" 
She threw another rock, her mind in turmoil.  "`^Does that rock ever 
think about being up here again?  No.  I don't have to think about 
being back there either.``"

--`@R`#P`6D`^a`6n``
~
