Sender  Marhault~
Date    Thu Jul 25 23:12:38 2002~
Stamp   1027656758
To      all~
Subject Introspect, a Quest in Review~
Text
``  Marhault sat down at the dock behind the Aegis Inn late at night, 
looking out at the water as thoughts and memories of the night's events
swam through his sadly unprepared mind.  Under an hour before, the 
hidden grove nearby had been a battleground of classic Good vs. Evil 
gone wrong.  Sirus Mekari, the Sonic Knight who had trained him to be 
the good man he now was, had been pushed off the proverbial ledge into 
a madness that made him the Ebon Knight.  Erik Lightsbane, Sirus's 
rival and demonic evil-doer challenged him there.  Several fighters and 
sorcerers - Marhault included - looked on as the two arch-rivals 
battled, each fighting for an unfamiliar side.

``  Intermitantly throughout the fight, Mekari had launched attacks at 
the group of adventurers looking on.  Marhault stood as their defence 
against his former friend and teacher, pained by the attack on his mind
and soul.  In the end, there was no winner.  Erik and Sirus had decided
that the fight would not be decided there.  The Ebon Knight, however, 
had something more for the whole group.  His soul-stealing attack of 
divine cleansing would have killed the group, were it not for 
Lightsbane standing in its way, and Marhault's magic defending against 
the rest.  Yoiko wasted no time, using her ability "All Creation" to 
mutilate Sirus, turning him half to bone-and-ash at her own personal 
injury.  The Ebon Knight made his exit, leaving the group to plan their
next move.  And leaving Marhault to sort out where he stood.

``  He looked out at the lake.  Where did he stand?  Sirus Mekari had 
made Marhault into the man he was now.  A good man, one unafraid to 
fight for the well-being of others.  Was this insanity a glimpse of 
things to come in his own life?  Would he turn his back and his sword 
upon those people he now believed in protecting?  Fearing his own 
insecurity, the sorcerer made his decision.  He would continue 
protecting those in need.  It was, perhaps, his destiny.  What his life
was always meant to be.  But...there would be time for that later.  Now 
was the time when he must solve his own problems...and save the Sonic 
Knight.  ... ... ...  If he can.

--`@R`#P`6D`^a`6n``
~
