Subject It comes.~
Text
`7     The sky was empty, clear, a pleasant blue and a few wisps of clouds.

`7     It began that way.  The spring air was crisp and scented with flowers, 
`7     and the birds chirped merrily without knowing any better.  Not that
`7     anyone could know what was to come, could forsee where the terror
`7     would focus its one, lidless eye.  Watching tirelessly, it awaits for
`7     the hour of Awakening, when old horrors would stir from their long
`7     slumber and direct the madness that is Chaos once more.

`7   The ground quivered as if beset by some great force.  The long plains
`7   beyond Narshe were covered in red and black broiling clouds, churning
`7   angrily and searing the grass it passed over.  Bolts of lightning arc
`7   across the brimming surface, tearing rampant paths through the burning
`7   fields.  From within the turmoil come gutteral cries and the haunting
`7   howls of the warp's denizens.  Like a wave of darkness pour fourth the
`7   hoardes of Chaos, sweeping towards Narshe and leaving a sickened land
`7   in their wake.

`7   Merely minutes later the sky darkens as thousands of pods fill it, and
`7   like a meteor shower they rain down mercilessly upon the Earth, beating
`7   angrily against the ground.  Like the pounding of great drums they fall
`7   against the surface with a resounding '`8DOOM!``' On and on it goes, '`8DOOM``
`8   DOOM DOOM!``' until their numbers crowd the ground with barely ten feet
`7   between them.  Silence blankets the area for a few seconds and then the
`7   pods unlock with a quiet hiss and open, blooming outwards like a giant
`7   field of flowers.  A contingent of marines file out from each one, each
`7   group filing into perfect formation with an eerie precision.  A single
`7   captain stands at the front of his squad, ignoring the buzz of tactical
`7   information streaming into his helmet.  He clicks the radio off and
`7   looks over his hardened troop.  A certain uneasiness gripped his mind
`7   that was uncommon for him to have right before battle, even with the
`7   vile forces of Chaos.  He recalled the words of one of the company's
`7   chaplains, an old and disturbed man, but well known for his clarity of
`7   vision.  Those words troubled the captain's heart...

`7          '`^..nature will be torn asunder.. ``'
`7          '`^..raped of natural order..``'
`7          '`^..time chained to demonic whim..``'
`7          '`^..great hands carve a path..``'
`7          '`^..for the carnal horror..``'

`7          '`^..whispers of Slaanesh..``'
`7          '`^..touch our comrades' minds..``'
`7          '`^..his eternal dream given form..``'
`7          '`^..as our waking nightmare...``'

`7   The captain remembered most clearly the chaplain's last words.

`7          '`^Emperor guide us...``
`7                              `^...the storm approaches.``'

`&Kurusa. `8- `&The Dark Millennium begins tonight, Friday the 26th at 5pm
`&          or 6pm pacific, depending on the turn out.  You do not want
`&          to miss this one.``
~
