Sender  Yoiko~
Date    Sun Jul 28 22:51:07 2002~
Stamp   1027914667
To      sirus~
Subject Soul searching~
Text
Those words.. they struck me deep.

They struck deeper than I let on.. even to myself. An old pain that never went
Away. Sometimes I wonder if I told him, would things have gone different?

Perhaps not. No one ever stays with me forever.
==========

Yoiko stared down at the sheet of paper she wrote those words on, squeezing her
eyes shut tightly. "`^Why do I feel this way.. after all this time?``" She asked
herself aloud, not expecting any reply. "`^..Maybe it isn't he who should die..``
`^but me instead.``"

Crumbling up the paper, Yoiko threw it against the wall angrily. Staring at her
hands, her eyes welled up with tears as memories of a time long past haunted her
every thought. "`^Not even the woman he remembered.. all I am is a joke..``" She
murmered, wiping her eyes quickly with her arm. "`^I haven't even told him that``
`^his daughter's alive and well...``"

Standing, Yoiko sighed softly. "`^Not that it matters.. he wants to kill me.``" She
said with a soft sigh before sitting to write again. Just as quickly, she rose
once more. "`^All of them.. they care about him enough to convince him to live..``
`^But for me.. no one mourns my death. No one ever will.``"

Turning her head, Yoiko stared over at the two swords in the corner of the room.
Her prized weapons that she once wielded by her side. She walked over, picking
them both up and testing their familiar weight. "`^...They want you back so bad..``
`^Well.. there's something we must do first, Rekki-maru and Mekki-maru.``" She says
softly, sheathing both blades. "`^If things are to be right between sirus and I..``
`^One of us must die.``"
~
Sender  Altera~
Date    Mon Jul 29 10:16:14 2002~
Stamp   1027955774
To      all~
Subject Crash Landing~
Text
``  Detective Altera Mitori of the Galaxy Police awoke and looked around.
She was lying on the floor of the bridge of her ship, Tolari.  The 
power was down, and buzzing electrical sound of severed wires rung 
through the smoky air.  Sitting up, she tried to recall what had landed
her in such a situation.  She remembered her assignment: she was to 
investigate the appearance of unindentifiable ships in orbit of earth. 
It wasn't a mission they'd give to just anyone...to do anything  
involving earth, you had to be known for good service to the GP.  
Afterall, with the limit of Galaxy Police influence in the area, one 
stranded on earth or anywhere within its solar system had little hope 
of rescue.
``  What had happened?  Altera remembered approaching earth in her ship.
She had just begun scanning for the foreign spacecraft when something 
else began to show on her sensors.  The ship warned her of a space 
anomoly directly in her path to orbit.  Activating the monitors, she 
was able to see a large space creature, unlike anything in the GP 
Archives.  Before she could take any evasive manuevers, the creature 
had fired on her, shooting small laser-like energy beams from its 
mouth.  She had managed to pull up some, dodging a few of the beams, 
but the thrusters took all that was left, leaving her ship motionless.
The monster began charging a more powerful blast.  Altera, in a 
last-ditch effort, had fired her heavy cannon, using the recoil to push 
her away from the monster, and inadvertantly forcing herself into 
Earth's orbit.  The creature fired its blast wildly, distracted by the 
injury it took from the heavy cannon.  The hit to Tolari caused 
irreparable damage, and all remaining power had been routed to life 
support as the ship plummeted to earth.
``  Altera looked upon her ship, now outside.  There was smoke which 
seemed to be pouring from every opening of the craft, especially the 
large hole in its side.  Tolari would never fly again.  Altera looked 
down at her command cube, as if hoping for advice.  She received none.
With no food supply, nowhere to stay, and no earth money, she knew she 
would have a hard time getting by, but somehow, she knew she would have
to manage.  She would find herself a job somewhere, make some money and 
get a place to stay.  Afterall...Galaxy Police Headquarters was bound 
to know she was missing after a while, and then they would come rescue
her.  All she had to do was send the distress signal.  She turned a few
sides of the pink, transparent command cube, and a light went on inside
it, indicating that the call had been sent.  Now, it was just a matter 
of waiting for a Galaxy Police ship to pick it up and come to her 
rescue.  "`^It can't be too long.......right?``"

--`@R`#P`6D`^a`6n``
~
