Sender  Marhault~
Date    Mon Jul 29 11:32:43 2002~
Stamp   1027960363
To      Sirus~
Subject A learning experience.~
Text
``  Marhault tore a sheet of paper from his notebook and looked at it, 
pen in hand.  Now was his rest period.  He had spent several days  
following Sirus, continually casting spells to make himself 
undetectable to the Ebon Knight.  Now he had no expendable magic power 
left to use.  He had to rest for some time, letting that energy return 
to him.  He tapped the pen against his desk, deciding what to do.

``  He sat there for nearly an hour, staring, until his pen began to move.
"`3Alone, I wonder how I ought to be
I sit here, with my pen in front of me.
I feel like I am powerless to fight
The forces that o'ertake my friend like night.``"

``  Marhault shook his head, "`^This is crap.  And a waste of my time, 
too.  I should be out making sure he doesn't hurt anyone, but here I am 
writing some rediculous prose.  I -hate- that I can't do anything...``"

"`3I learned in days before what I must do
But now I cannot practice what I knew.
My thoughts and feelings I wish I'd omit,

``  Marhault shook his head again, looking down at the paper.  He stared
at it for some time, the final line missing from his attempt at a poem. 
"`^This really IS a waste of my time!``" 

`3And I just found out I can't write worth shit.``"

--`@R`#P`6D`^a`6n``
~
Sender  Jades~
Date    Mon Jul 29 22:38:06 2002~
Stamp   1028000286
To      sirus erik~
Subject writing quest~
Text
Ebonsgrace hums malevolently as it slices through the air violently,
blood spraying everywhere.  The frantic screams linger in the air but
die down to silence as bodies thud to the ground heavily.  She glances
around herself quickly, her narrow crimson colored eyes glowing in
the moonlight.  Thrown around her body is a long onyx shaded shroud
that dances amidst her torso in the wind.  The rest of her attire matches
that of the night sky, a black tank top and cargo pants.  Thick soled
combat boots shuffle through the dirt as the woman walks towards
one of the bodies that seems to have vital signs left.  Reaching
down with a pale hand, she grabs the young man by his neck and
stands up slowly, lifting the weighted body with ease.  Startled, the
man opens his eyes widely, staring at the strange woman.  He
attempts to scream, but the hand at his throat tightens, the noise
quickly muffled.  A sick grin spreads across the young womans lips
as she tilts her head to one side, examining the man curiously.

Quietly she says in a raspy tone, '`1Ah yes, we all make mistakes, don't we?``'
She pauses for a moment and continues, '`1Tis a shame that this one wil be your last.``'

With that, the grip on the young mans throat tightens as the woman
pulls him towards her.  The moonlight glistens upon her long slender
fangs, before she plunges them deeply into the poor man's nubile flesh.
She feeds ravenously, sucking the lifeblood from the mans body for
a few moments, then pulls the now limp body from her mouth.  With
a flick of her right wrist she snaps the neck of the victim like a
toothpick, then tosses his body carelessly to the ground.  She dries
her mouth with a dark sleeve of her shroud, while flipping her sword
around with her left hand, the blood sliding off, leaving the blade
untainted.  She resheathes Ebonsgrace upon her backside and
begins to walk away from the carnage.

A male voice calls out from the darkness, '`8Very good Jades.  You're
`8learning quite well.``'

He chuckles deeply and floats down, landing, joining Jades by her side.
They walk together for a few moments along the moonlit path.

She replies quietly, a few minutes later, '`1Indeed.  For once I didn't
`1need your assistance, dear Erik.``'

She flashes a quick grin at him, but he just shrugs it off.

Erik says hastily, '`8Come, lets go.  Daybreak will be hitting soon.``'

The young vampire nods, as her feet lift from the ground.  The
demon, outstretches his massive black feathered wings, taking
flight as well.  They vanish into the darkness, only the sound
of wings flapping can be heard, which is quickly drowned out, by
the whipping of the wind.
~
