Sender  Citan~
Date    Tue Jul 30 14:10:34 2002~
Stamp   1028056234
To      all~
Subject Where the hell is Citan?!~
Text
......
Darkness....black....an infinite sea of nothing...
Darkness....black....an infinite sea of nothing...
Does the world exist? ....do you? .....do I??.....Who Am I?
"`5Citan...Citan Uzuki....awaken, bold warrior of the light...``"
The voice is faint at first, as though part of a dream, or very far away.
"`5Citan....you must come back....``"
Gradually the voice becomes more insistant, more forceful...yet at the same time more gentle and comforting.
"`%CITAN.``"
Citan Uzuki awoke...and was instantly confused. There seemed to be no directions, no up or down...nothing...Except for her.
A beautiful woman with a radiant smile, whose eyes seemed to see everything and accept it all, without exception. It took Citan 10 minutes to realize he was staring.
"`^Ummm...who are you....and where are we?``"
"`%I have been called many things over the course of human history, but in truth, I have no name. As for where we are....we are nowhere...we "aren't", if you will.``"
Citan shook his head, feeling dazed and confused. "`^Uh...ok, what am I not doing here?``"
The woman looked at Citan and giggled a bit, then took a step closer, enticing, alluring, sexy and cute all at once. "`%I am happy to see that you still have a sense of humor, my Paladin, considering all that has happened.``"
Citan got a sense of foreboding, dreading the answer but knowing he had to ask... "`^What do you mean?``"
She got a worried look. "`%I am sorry, my champion, but time is short. All you need to know for the moment is that I brought you here to save you from death....and now you must go.``"
"`^Hey! Wait just a mimmmph?!?!``"
At that moment, the woman kissed him, muffling all protest before fading away.
At the kiss, Citan felt an inner light flowing into him, calming him.
"`%Farewell, my Paladin, I've given you what aid I can. It is up to you now...until we meet again.``"
With these words echoing in his head, Citan suddenly found himself in the ashes of Kansas.
~
