Subject Character Thoughts~
Text
Yombo is not sure about the past, the past of Sirus, Marhault, or any of the others involved in this.  She is but a child to most of them by comparison.
She is unsure of whom to trust, for she does not know on which side each stands.  Erik, whom she battled against weeks...days before, seems different now, but still not trust worthy.
She sighs.  Marhault is one who she can trust.  He cares for Sirus very much and it is very evident.
Then there's Althena, whom she just met, has a deep connection to Sirus and Yombo feels that she too can be trusted.  There is one thing that she knows for sure, and that is to help Sirus realize what he is not.
She nods to herself.

"`^I will do what I can, say what I must, but give up I will not,``" she says quietly out loud to herself.  She knows what it's like to wonder why people care for her, because she asks the same questions herself.
She once thought that no one loved her, no one cared.  She left home when she was 8 years old, knowing her parents would never let her train as a mage, she hasn't been back since.
But Jekira convinced her to call home, and she did.  Now she knows that her parents care...and love her...and it filled the void inside her...and gave her a warm feeling inside.
"`^I will make sure that Sirus feels this too...because he is a good person and deserves to feel this feeling``" she says to no one as she lies in her bed thinking.

Sometimes, Yombo thinks that she is in over her head.  She sighs slightly.
"`^I know I am younger than most of the others, but my heart is still in the right place.  I just hope I live through all of this.``"
She says biting her lower lip pensively.
"`^Everything will work out okay, and Sirus will be back to his old self...or maybe he will be a better self.``"  She smiles at this and wonders when something else will come up that she will be needed for.
But there is one thing that she is afraid of most, not the fear of dying, the fear that her inexperience will get someone killed...someone she cares for...or someone who is also trying to help.

"`^I'll just have to train harder then,``" she says to the ceiling.  She closes her eyes to go to sleep.
Unaware of what is to come...or the outcome of this situation that she got herslf involved in.  But she will see through it till the end...the end of her life..or the problem...which ever comes first.


Well there is my characters thoughts.

`&Yombo - `8A day will come when the sun longer shines, and that will be the end.....and she...will be longer.``
~
Sender  Ruka~
