To      sirus~
Subject Thoughts.~
Text
`    Ruka sits on the end of the pier, watching the water ripple with the
light morning breeze. She reaches a hand down to the water and touches it,
watching the concentric rings from impact of her fingers spread until they
fade away. She sighs in relaxation and lies down on her stomach, idly play-
ing with the water and purring to herself contentedly. Somewhere in the back
of her mind, Salamander expresses his amusement at her mood, but she brushes
off his teasing comments, used to ignoring him.
`    -`1It's kind of funny, everyone's so tense.``- She thinks softly.
`    -`1And you're not, hm? Well you HAVE been pasted to the ceiling for the
last couple of days, you know.``- Salamander snickers.
`    -`1Hush, mutt.``-
`    -`1Bah, can't I tease even a LITTLE?``-
`    -`1I'm wondering what's going to happen with Sirus. It's an interesting
situation.``- Ruka muses.
`    -`1I take that as a no.``- Salamander grumbles, sulking quietly in a back
corner of her mind.
`    -`1It's probably too much to hope for that he has come to his senses in
any way of a permanent basis, but you never know. I wonder...``-
`    Salamander expresses a flicker of interest. -`1Wonder what?``-
`    -`1What Legis has in mind for all this. Fighting Sirus right now would be
rather counterproductive, don't you think?``-
`    -`1Indeed. We'll see.``-
`    -`1Could be fun.``-
`    Salamander murmers his agreement, then the warm feel of his conciousness
fades into the background. After a few silent moments, Ruka returns to play-
ing with the water, purring to herself as she contemplates the excitement to
come.
~
