To      Sirus~
Subject A momment of reflection~
Text
Stretching in the chair. He always enjoyed the Sushi bar late at night. He had managed to
convince Esme to let him in later for a small fee. Pity he couldn't eat the Sushi anymore he remebered 
it fondly. Focusing on business. "`^Things are going well``" he thinks as he ponders recent events. 
Grinning as he thinks about the soon to happen job, and his employer...Oh there faces are going to 
be quite lovely when they see his little surprize. Stifling a chuckle in the silent room, his mind 
wanders to the new and more complicated aspects of his life. The smell...the feel..Taking his thoughts 
firmly and thrusting them to the side. "`^Now is not the time for that``" He says to no one, pushing 
those new and dangerous thoughts away. He nods to Esme who smiles back to him knowingly.
"`^Dinner``" he thinks "`^Maybe Later``". Now for Sirus. Oh yes that would be the most fun. No one 
will expect his cunning offer. The Ebon Knight maybe fledgling in his evil, but with a guiding hand, a 
few choice events and he will be sealed to his path, and no soul would expect that allience not a 
single one. This time unable to control his diabolic chuckle.  speaking softly to himself "`^Oh 
yes...that will be so fun...all he has to do is say yes..``". Gettng up from his seat he smiles to Esme. He 
adjust his coat as he walks out into the chill night air. He spots a raver girl staggering down the street 
among some friends. the last thing he thinks before walking towards them is "`^Dinner is served``"

Legis Harden sings, '`^Not to loud, Don't tell everybody, Don't give away the game``'
~
