To      Sirus~
Subject Poem~
Text
I sit in the bar
The black walls fall into even darker corners
One window with a never ending view but constraining glass.
I sit so still that I hope to feel my heart beat
But for it to beat would require a soul
He took my soul
I turn my face from the shining sun
I'm only 20
There are no prizes.
but I shall have my revenge.
~
