To      all~
Subject Rescue Mission~
Text
The vampire hunters gathered inside the cell where Rujin was last kept. Due to the
continued vampire menace, and Botouden's abcense to reclaim Argyle, no one knew of
the young vampire's whereabouts. The vampire insurrection was quelled, murderers
like Serith disappeared into the shadows, The Vampire Hunters had won the battle
for Neo-Tokyo. It had been a week since the disappearance of Rujin, when Botouden
suddenly returned to the headquarters for no apparent reason. Informing the rest
of his comrades to Rujin's imprisonment, we circle back to the beginning of this
story, the murderers of murderers stood within the cell staring at the wall.

Koren was called to investigate the room, much to her displeasure it seemed. Within
Koren discovered the ethereal remenants of a gate. Using her powers to re-open the
passage, they discovered where Rujin was held... in Hell. The screams of torture
and eternal agony reverberated beyond the afterlife through the old factory, shrill
blood curdling cries for salvation. These wails waivered the resolve of some, but
but not substantially enough to halt the march into the universe of pain. The portal
lead the clan members onto the rim of the Seventh Circle, that of burning sand. The
fellowship quickly made thier way to the Causeway over Malebolge, and were greeted 
with a large demon, prodding and puncturing a forsaken soul wielding a pitchfork.

the demons of the clan had only to converse with the beast a moment before they
obtained the location of thier missing vampire. Held Beneath the giant centaur, Cacus,
They began to make their way down the pass to the creature. The met resistance immediatly.
hands grasping at them from all sides, hands from the Malebolge, hands from the skin 
of Hell itself. Clawing and dragging them into the Bolgia to join the torment of
those below.

To Be Continued...

`1R`!u`#j`!i`1n `8- `6"`^You are surrounded by a horde of marauding sand dwarves looking to rob``
`^you.`6" `8- `6"`^Heres the plan... we are going to lie through our teeth!`6"``
~
Sender  Rujin~
Date    Mon Aug 19 17:15:26 2002~
Stamp   1029795326
To      all~
Subject Exodus~
Text
The appendages born of agony grasped and fought at thier prey. The Vampire Hunters,
not being a group to fold quickly under pressure, fought back. Koren and Xanretsu
took to the smog and ash filled air, but they did not escape the grasp of the hands.
the arms stretched into indomitably long, prehensile, cords that snapped at the two
furiously. Fascreth, Mareth, and Kamali continued the revolt on the ground. Soon
finding themselves having to scramble from the Bolgias, being cast into the rivers
excrement and blood. Not too far ahead of the struggling band stood the hellspawn
Cacus. The five desperately charged for him, only to be held back by an inconceivable
amount of arms and fingers. As the snare began to close on the heroes, The arms quickly
retreated. Disappearing back into the Bolgia and walls. The hunters didn't think
much of this event, making a mad dash to the Centaur, only to be met with new devilry...
Kaoseraph.

The demon beast was more then confident challanging the whole team to a fight, the
demons and the dwarf were quick to oblige. They're queries and assault for Rujin's
location were met with godlike force. Fascreth's being was stitched into time, he
became like still life, catatonic. Koren attempted a spell, and was turned to stone.
Mareth's evade and attack met a counter offensive. Mareth was disarmed, brutally
knocked unconscious then tossed aside like a child. Kamali stabbed into the extremely
dense hide of the devil, with no effect, he was crushed like a bug. Xanretsu disappeared
immediately making his way to Cacus, the guardian of Rujin.  Though overpoweringly
strong, mentally Kaoseraph didn't possess much. Koren unlocked Fascreth and herself.
The female magician took back to the air to catch up to her comrade, Fascreth distracted
the demon beast. Kaoseraph and Fascreth traded blow for blow, Koren and Xanretsu
bargained with Cacus for the right to retrieve Rujin.

The Centaur quickly allowed them passage, wanting to find a way to rate Kaoseraph's
personal attention. Rujin was held within some sort of bloody, runic, holding spell.
Koren worked to undo the conjuration, Fascreth continued to entertain Kaoseraph,
enduring mountain crumbling strikes. Koren undid the spell without much effort when
she discovered the key to it, Xanretsu freed Rujin from the burning sand and the
two left the Bolgia, returning to the combat area. Fascreth, with the assistance
of the mysterious reappearance of Mareth, converged for a last ditch effort, knocking
Kaoseraph off his guard and temporarily indisposed. The clan fled from Hell, as fast
as any sane soul would, given the chance.

OOC: That is the Reader's Digest version of this RP. 

`1R`!u`#j`!i`1n `8- `6'`^I made this mess now it's over...`6'``
~
