Text
``   Elliot Smith leaned back in his chair, weaving his arms together across
his chest. `^"`6Well, our special operations team has already landed in Tokyo.
It'll just be a matter of time before plan is set in motion.`^"
``   Mr. Smith's guest grinned widely. `^"`6That's good to hear.`^"``
``   `^"`6Though...`^"`` Elliot sat forward. `^"`6I'm slightly puzzled as to why you
wanted Commander Ezekiel Luziend to head this mission. I mean, considering the 
'incident' with the Midnight Sun, I would think you'd want him out of the GSE 
project. At the very least, out of such a delicate and important operation.`^"``
``   The guest levelled his eyesight with Mr. Smith, making Elliot cringe slightly.
`^"`6Nonsense... he's perfect for the job, which is why I had him lead Kthalu GUN
in the first place.`^"``
``   `^"`6I just think--`^"``
``   `^"`6You just think it's great.`^"`` The man stood from his chair. `^"`6I'll be there
with them, so there's no need for your worries. Nor would there be any need
if I wasn't there, because he's leading this mission, and that's my final
decision. I hope you understand, Mr. Smith.`^"``
``   Mr. Smith fell back in his seat. `^"`6Y-yes, of course, sir.`^"``
``   The man smiled, baring all his polished teeth. `^"`6Good. I started the GSE,
and I intend to use and control all of it's aspects when it pleases me.`^"``
The man took his cane from beside the empty chair. `^"`6Now, if you will excuse
me, I have a flight to catch.`^"``


To be continued...
~
