To      Fatetaf~
Subject Questz0rs @ppl1ca7i0nz0rs. (I'm just kidding.)~
Text
So I'm this time travelling super ninja from the future with the power to destroy cities, control
other people with mere though....

So I'm playing this dragon. Serious, I'm actually a dragon, you can check. I'm one of them monk types
apparently, I'm 35 years old, although, if possible, I'd like to play something a little younger, 17-20ish
I'm just not mature enough for 35.

Alignment's chaotic good. I do what I think is right, but what I think is right isn't necessarily what
everyone else thinks is right.

Psst. Hey kid. Yeah, you. No, you don't know me, and you probably don't want to. But I need a favor,
and coin doesn't tell stories. Usually. Listen, in a few days, give or take, a girl's gonna wander into
your town. Not much older than you. You'll know her. She'll look about as lost as a bird out of the nest
for the first time, but if you ask, I don't doubt she'll be a damn sight to proud to accept help.
Here's where you come in. It's simple, really, I want you to slip an innkeeper a little something, make
he's amenable to letting her work off a couple nights room, and some food. Offer to show her around, since
she's new. Keep her away from the bad parts of town, just make 'em seem uninteresting. What? No, she doesn't
know me. It'd be best if you didn't say anything about it to her. I'll be around to make sure things
turn out the way I want. You understand?

Here's the deal. I'm not going anywhere special, and that's what's bothering me. Martyr without a cause
is even more apt than rebel. Every once in awhile, I'll see someone who makes me think of myself,
one way or another, and maybe I'll try and help 'em out of whatever mess they're in, but I don't make it a
habit. Most of my past was spent training and fighting, but when I learned all I could learn, I didn't
have a clue why I bothered, or what I had been readied for. Disgruntled and unpredictable doesn't begin to
describe. Who knows, it might actually be interesting.
~
Sender  Sirus~
Date    Fri Sep  6 14:12:57 2002~
Stamp   1031339577
To      all~
Subject "Walking backwards on the Sun"~
Text
The knight stood overlooking a great chasm, wherein he peered
down into the vast depths of the fall. He could not even see
the floor of the chasm. It was black, hollow... empty, just like
he himself was. Life, love, religion, freinds... everything in
his life had ripped him up, leaving nothing more then a hollow
shell of a man. A sword strapped to his back and ability to
inflict pain was all he had left. And that was by far, a fate
worse then death.

As he stood, certain lyrics swept across his mind. Words from
the harrowing anthem carassed his still beating black heart.

"`8I am just a worthless liar... I am just an imbecile...
I will only complicate you... Trust in me and fall as well...
I will find a center in you... I will chew it up and leave...
Trust me... Trust me...``"

As the night befall the face of the cliff where Sirus stood, his
eyes started to flicker with a small red glow, which died into a
dull glow, and eventually faded out.

"`^After all these years... have I become everything which I stand to
heal in this world? Too many people beleived in me, and I've taken
that faith and used it to rip my own soul out, to gift it to those
who own it more then I do. One last peace, before I fade away.``'

Sirus closed his eyes and a massive wind swept over him...
~
