Stamp   1032065323
To      Sirus~
Subject Re: Do you wanna die?~
Text
Well, erm... no. I'm going to deal with this subject on my own. Looking for an explination? Well, whatever.
Here's one anyway:

Kun was trapped in "another dimension", dare I steal it from dub Dragonball Z, by "Bryson", aka someone posing
as him. Needless to say, Kun was killed and turned into a Xokai warrior. BUT, a few nights before any of this
happened, I held a session in Aegis where the Inn was attacked by a swarm of SSiA members, and a helicopter
packing a deadly, as if this descriptive word is even needed, gatling gun. Kun happened to leap through the
windshield of this flying vehicle and kill both the passenger gunner and the pilot. Now, with the driver dead,
a detonator went off, causing the ship to explode a mile away from Aegis. Of course, Kun was thrown from the
chopper and left in a tree, bleeding profusely. When all seemed lost, a shadowy figure appeared and saved Kun,
"healing" his grave wounds like they were nothing to begin with. The stranger never said his name, even when
Kun questioned who he was, but without knowing where the hell I was going with this plot, I threw in a note
about the figure having the same voice as Kun himself.

Now, here's where it gets REALLY interesting.

The figure leaps away, and Kun goes back to Aegis, only to be Xokai'ed a few days later. However, I really did
NOT want to have Kun become Xokai. He's too awesome of a character for me to let go of so quickly. Having put
this idea of a shadowy figure with Kun's voice up in the air, I decided to take a route I never even planned.
The shadowy figure is... well, none other than Kun himself. Confused? Of course not. This is AnimeMUD. Heh,
well, to make a long story short, someone within the government has made a clone of Kun, the Xokai member that
is. He's reporting to someone he THINKS is Charles Daiko. The shadowy character is Real Kun. He's currently
in Russia, scouting a Xokai drop point. Both him and Daiko know about this clone, but they have no idea who
is involved, so they're lying down low. Now, there will come a time in this second Xokai war where Kun has to
face himself. The Xokai Kun looks like Real Kun does: suit, sword, yadda, MINUS the gun. Real Kun is decked
out in ninja garb, with the REAL Masamune he carries. When Xokai Kun falls, Real Kun's Beretta will come back
into play. I love the suited character I made too much to lose his classy look so soon.

So yeah, that's how it is. Did I lose you somewhere? I hope not. If you need any clearing up, note me, or
whatever the hell you wanna do to contact me. I'll be on from time to time.

Peace out.

`8Kun.``
~
