To      all~
Subject Demise of Megua~
Text
Let it be known:

Upon his daily business, Xrkyl was approached by a cloaked man.
The man gestured him to the side, into the shadows.  He revealed his face,
pale as the moon, with firey red eyes.  His name was Zekim, and was in
dire need of assistance.  He elaborated on the deeds of Megua, a
warrior of the realm.  Zekim explained how he was unjustly assaulted while he
was vulnerable, and stripped of his armor and dignity.

The story had not gone unheard, for upon mentioning the battle,
darkness enveloped the vicinity as Fascreth revealed his presence.  He too, 
had requested that Megua's actions do not go unpunished.

Zekim's plea was heard by the Judge council, backed by Fascreth's testimony.
Megua was to be brought to justice.  

Not long after the Judgement, Megua demanded Xrkyl's presence on the field
of combat.  Xrkyl accepted the challenge and slayed Megua in the dark woods.

The Judgement on Megua had been passed, and completed.  And so, Zekim's plight
had been avenged, but will long be forgotten.

X.
~
