Sender  Citan~
Date    Sun Sep 22 16:33:18 2002~
Stamp   1032730398
To      all~
Subject Forbidden Love~
Text
A young man with raven black hair walked into his superiors' office, a slightly confused look on his face.
His white cleric's robes swayed ever so slightly as he approached the man sitting behind the desk. "`^You...wanted to speak with me, Cardinal?``"
The cardinal turned. "`^Ah, Citan. Welcome. I trust your trip was a pleasent one.``" Citan nodded. "`^Good, good...Please, have a seat.``" The cardinal motioned toward the chairs in front of his desk.
There was a pause that seemed to go on for ages, while the Cardinal looked at a few papers...No, a file. Citan's file, in fact. Abruptly, the old Cardinal sighed and looked up at Citan.
"`^Now it has come to my attention that, some time ago you had extended periods of contact with a certain demoness...``"
Citan began to speak, but was silenced by a wave of the Cardinal's hand. "`^I'm not finished!...This individual...Siren...What is your relationship to her?``"
"`Siren? I don't know who that is...``"
The Cardinal frowned. "`^Do you honestly think so little of me? Think I'm blind? I'm aware of what went on between you, and because you show so much promise, I am willing to keep it strictly between us.``"
Citan chose his words carefully. "`^Your Grace...I honestly don't know who that is...``"
"`^Uzuki! I cannot help you if you choose to protect her like this!!....It's obvious that this 'girl' is a corruptive influence.``"
Citan sighed and bowed his head a bit. "`^Your Grace...It's not her fault that she is like that. She is the victim of a curse....``"
"`^Enough, Uzuki!!!``" He looked angry. "`^It is bad enough that you consorted with her at all!! Yes, I'm aware of her 'tragic' history, and that is no excuse for the monster she has become!!``"
The Cardinal stood and began to pace. "`^This puts us in a predicament, Uzuki, and a very unpleasant one at that. I'm afraid we must take steps.``"
"`^Steps, your Grace?``"
"`^Since you are so unwilling to do your sworn duty, I will handle it instead. Speak to noone else of this matter and it never happened.``"
Citan jumped to his feet in alarm.
"`^Your Grace, please reconsider!! She poses no real threat to the Church!``"
The Cardinal looked very annoyed with the young man. "`^HER EXISTENCE IS A THREAT!! The matter has been taken care of! An Etone has been sent to rectify your mistake and do what you could or would not do!``"
The words hit Citan like a brick wall. "`^ETONE!? YOU SENT AN ETONE!?!``" His infuriated face grew threatening. "`^Pray that no harm befalls her, your Grace....``" With that, Citan stormed out of the room, hoping he would be in time. "`^Pray....``"
~
Sender  Giko~
Date    Thu Sep 26 14:35:20 2002~
Stamp   1033068920
To      all~
Subject Driven~
Text
Giko had been training furiously day and night, with little or no sleep, he couldn't stand to waste the time it took.
The large room he used for training was currently set to simulate gravity 600 times earths normal gravity.
What he was doing was dangerous and slightly insane. He didn't care. He HAD to become stronger, he HAD TO!
The current program had him fighting a group of 3 heavily armed mecha...All of them had been set to be faster, stronger, and tougher than him in half this gravity...he was having problems.
He slammed his fist into one of them, then his other. He dented it's tough hide, but it took a piece of his when it kicked him across the room then blasted him...He still didn't care.
Shiori's words came back to him. "`5Just stay with your family``"..."`5You're much too weak``"..."`5Im a goddess, I'll handle it.``"..."`5You dont know the true extent of my powers, monkey.``"
"`^DAMN YOU!!!``"
He leapt up and charged again, narrowly avoiding the mecha's attacks. He grabbed its arm, and tore it out of the socket...and was caught up in an attack by the things teammates.
He heard the taunting voice again. "`5You'll never gain strength unless you get rid of your anger.``"
He was barely aware of the fact that he had just taken an incredible beating...Maybe it was lack of sleep and food...maybe it was insanity...but he had been hearing her voice constantly, a taunting, superior tone that seemed to always mock him.
"`5We don't need the help of someone who's whole race was destroyed due to their collective stupidity.``"
"`^Goddess...what a joke...I'll show her what anger can do...show all of them!!``"
He attacked the mechs in a blind rage paying little attention to the beatings he took, or to the blood he lost.
It didn't matter, none of it did...he had to reach the next level...he had to defeat Cort...he had to know how so many people he knew were so much stronger than him, why he, Giko, a Prince of Vegeta, was so weak, so pathetic.
And most importantly, he HAD TO MAKE THAT INFURIATING LIZARD WOMAN SHUT HER FUCKING MOUTH.
He should have been paying more attention, because he was knocked to his knees and then kicked in the head. Hunger and sleeplessness was taking it's toll on him...he felt so tired...He had lost too much blood.
His vision blurred, and he blacked out. The last thing he saw were the mechs closing in on him.
"`5...Just a monkey after all.``"
~
